72 /* shared data : this is used during genlocale process
73  * data shared by several locales are centralized here; and saved only once
74  * in the generated libray */
75 typedef enum
76 {
77  LOC_SHARED_COLLATION = 0,
78  LOC_SHARED_ALPHABET = 1,
79  LOC_SHARED_NORMALIZATION = 2
80 } LOC_SHARED_DATA_TYPE;
81 
82 typedef struct
83 {
84  LOC_SHARED_DATA_TYPE lsd_type;
85  char lsd_key[COLL_NAME_SIZE];
86 
87 /* print size of an integer */
88 #define COLL_SHARED_DATA_SIZE (10 + 2)
89  void *data;
90  LDML_CONTEXT ldml_context;
91 } LOC_SHARED_DATA;

210 #define PRINT_DEBUG_START(d, a, m, s) \
211  do { \
212  print_debug_start_el (d, a, m, s); \
213  } while (0);
214 
215 #define PRINT_DEBUG_END(d, m, s) \
216  do { \
217  print_debug_end_el (d, m, s); \
218  } while (0);
219 
220 #define PRINT_DEBUG_DATA(d, m, s) \
221  do { \
222  print_debug_data_content (d, m, s); \
223  } while (0);
224 
225 #define PRINT_TO_C_FILE_MAX_INT_LINE 10
226 
227 #if defined(_WIN32) || defined(WINDOWS) || defined(WIN64)
228 #define DLL_EXPORT_PREFIX "__declspec(dllexport) "
229 #define LOCLIB_FILE_EXT "dll"
230 #else
231 #define DLL_EXPORT_PREFIX ""
232 #define LOCLIB_FILE_EXT "so"
233 #endif
234 
235 #define PRINT_STRING_TO_C_FILE(fp, val, len) \
236  do { \
237  int istr; \
238  fprintf (fp, "\""); \
239  for (istr = 0; istr < len; istr++) \
240  { \
241  fprintf (fp, "\\x%02X", (unsigned char) val[istr]); \
242  } \
243  fprintf (fp, "\""); \
244  } while (0);
245 
246 #define PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE(fp, type, valname, val, format, d) \
247  do { \
248  fprintf (fp, "\n" DLL_EXPORT_PREFIX "const " \
249  type " " valname "_%s = " format ";\n", d, val); \
250  } while (0);
251 
252 #define PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE(fp, valname, val, d) \
253  do { \
254  fprintf (fp, "\n" DLL_EXPORT_PREFIX "const char " valname "_%s[] = ", d); \
255  PRINT_STRING_TO_C_FILE (fp, val, strlen (val)); \
256  fprintf (fp, ";\n"); \
257  } while (0);
258 
259 #define PRINT_STRING_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE(fp, valname, arrcount, val, d) \
260  do { \
261  int istrarr; \
262  fprintf(fp, "\n" DLL_EXPORT_PREFIX"const char* " valname "_%s[] = {\n", d);\
263  for (istrarr = 0; istrarr < arrcount; istrarr++) \
264  { \
265  fprintf(fp, "\t"); \
266  PRINT_STRING_TO_C_FILE (fp, val[istrarr], strlen(val[istrarr])); \
267  if (istrarr < arrcount - 1) \
268  { \
269  fprintf(fp, ",\n"); \
270  } \
271  else \
272  { \
273  fprintf(fp, "\n"); \
274  } \
275  } \
276  fprintf(fp, "};\n"); \
277  } while (0);
278 
279 
280 #define PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE(fp, vname, vtype, intf, arrcount, val, d) \
281  do { \
282  int i_arr, j_arr; \
283  fprintf(fp, \
284  "\n" DLL_EXPORT_PREFIX "const " vtype " " vname "_%s[] = {\n", d); \
285  j_arr = 1; \
286  for (i_arr = 0; i_arr < arrcount; i_arr++) \
287  { \
288  fprintf(fp, "\t"); \
289  fprintf(fp, intf, val[i_arr]); \
290  if (i_arr < arrcount - 1) \
291  { \
292  fprintf(fp, ","); \
293  } \
294  j_arr++; \
295  if (j_arr > PRINT_TO_C_FILE_MAX_INT_LINE) \
296  { \
297  j_arr = 1; \
298  fprintf(fp, "\n"); \
299  } \
300  } \
301  fprintf(fp, "};\n"); \
302  } while (0);
303 
304 
305 #define PRINT_UNNAMED_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE(fp, intf, tab, arrcount, val) \
306  do { \
307  int i_uarr, j_uarr; \
308  fprintf(fp, tab"{\n"); \
309  j_uarr = 1; \
310  for (i_uarr = 0; i_uarr < arrcount; i_uarr++) \
311  { \
312  fprintf(fp, intf, val[i_uarr]); \
313  if (i_uarr < arrcount - 1) \
314  { \
315  fprintf(fp, ","); \
316  } \
317  j_uarr++; \
318  if (j_uarr > PRINT_TO_C_FILE_MAX_INT_LINE) \
319  { \
320  j_uarr = 1; \
321  fprintf(fp, "\n" tab); \
322  } \
323  } \
324  fprintf(fp, "\n" tab "}"); \
325  } while (0);

878 /*
879  * start_element_ok() - Dummy XML element start function
880  * Used just for verbose purpose.
881  *
882  * return: always 0 (validation OK)
883  * data: user data
884  * attr: attribute/value pair array
885  *
886  * Note : this function is registered by XML elements that normally do not
887  * require any validation for element start, but is used only for
888  * debug purpose, in order to properly display each parsed XML element
889  */
890 static int
891 start_element_ok (void *data, const char **attr)
892 {
893  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "", 0);
894  return 0;
895 }
896 
897 /*
898  * end_element_ok() - Dummy XML element end function
899  * Used just for verbose purpose.
900  *
901  *
902  * return: always 0 (OK)
903  * data: user data
904  * el_name: element name
905  *
906  * Note : this function is registered by XML elements that normally do not
907  * require any action for element end, but is used only for
908  * debug purpose, in order to properly display each parsed XML element
909  */
910 static int
911 end_element_ok (void *data, const char *el_name)
912 {
913  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "", 0);
914  return 0;
915 }
916 
917 /*
918  * start_calendar() - XML element start function
919  * "ldml dates calendars calendar"
920  *
921  * return: 0 validation OK enter this element , 1 validation NOK do not enter
922  * -1 error abort parsing
923  * data: user data
924  * attr: attribute/value pair array
925  */
926 static int
927 start_calendar (void *data, const char **attr)
928 {
929  if (xml_check_att_value (attr, "type", "gregorian") != 0)
930  {
931  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "", 1);
932  return 1;
933  }
934 
935  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "", 0);
936  return 0;
937 }
938 
939 /*
940  * end_dateFormatCUBRID() - XML element end function
941  * "ldml dates calendars calendar dateFormatCUBRID"
942  *
943  * return: 0 parser OK, non-zero value if parser NOK and stop parsing
944  * data: user data
945  * el_name: element name
946  */
947 static int
948 end_dateFormatCUBRID (void *data, const char *el_name)
949 {
950  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
951  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
952 
953  assert (data != NULL);
954 
955  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
956 
957  /* copy data buffer to locale */
958  assert (ld->data_buf_count < (int) sizeof (ld->dateFormat));
959 
960  if (ld->data_buf_count < (int) sizeof (ld->dateFormat))
961  {
962  strcpy (ld->dateFormat, ld->data_buffer);
963  }
964  else
965  {
966  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "Too much data", -1);
967  return -1;
968  }
969 
970  clear_data_buffer ((XML_PARSER_DATA *) data);
971 
972  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "", 0);
973 
974  return 0;
975 }
976 
977 /*
978  * end_timeFormatCUBRID() - XML element end function
979  * "ldml dates calendars calendar timeFormatCUBRID"
980  *
981  * return: 0 parser OK, non-zero value if parser NOK and stop parsing
982  * data: user data
983  * el_name: element name
984  */
985 static int
986 end_timeFormatCUBRID (void *data, const char *el_name)
987 {
988  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
989  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
990 
991  assert (data != NULL);
992 
993  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
994 
995  /* copy data buffer to locale */
996  assert (ld->data_buf_count < (int) sizeof (ld->timeFormat));
997 
998  if (ld->data_buf_count < (int) sizeof (ld->timeFormat))
999  {
1000  strcpy (ld->timeFormat, ld->data_buffer);
1001  }
1002  else
1003  {
1004  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "Too much data", -1);
1005  return -1;
1006  }
1007 
1008  clear_data_buffer ((XML_PARSER_DATA *) data);
1009 
1010  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "", 0);
1011 
1012  return 0;
1013 }
1014 
1015 /*
1016  * end_datetimeFormatCUBRID() - XML element end function
1017  * "ldml dates calendars calendar datetimeFormatCUBRID"
1018  *
1019  * return: 0 parser OK, non-zero value if parser NOK and stop parsing
1020  * data: user data
1021  * el_name: element name

1298 /*
1299  * start_month() - XML element start function
1300  * "ldml dates calendars calendar months monthContext monthWidth month"
1301  *
1302  * return: 0 validation OK enter this element , 1 validation NOK do not enter
1303  * -1 error abort parsing
1304  * data: user data
1305  * attr: attribute/value pair array
1306  */
1307 static int
1308 start_month (void *data, const char **attr)
1309 {
1310  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
1311  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
1312  char *month_count = NULL;
1313 
1314  assert (data != NULL);
1315 
1316  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
1317 
1318  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "type", &month_count) == 0)
1319  {
1320  assert (month_count != NULL);
1321  ld->curr_period = atoi (month_count);
1322 
1323  assert (ld->curr_period > 0 && ld->curr_period <= CAL_MONTH_COUNT);
1324 
1325  if (ld->curr_period > 0 && ld->curr_period <= CAL_MONTH_COUNT)
1326  {
1327  ld->curr_period = ld->curr_period - 1;
1328  }
1329  else
1330  {
1331  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "Invalid month", -1);
1332  return -1;
1333  }
1334 
1335  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "", 0);
1336  return 0;
1337  }
1338 
1339  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "", 1);
1340  return 1;
1341 }

1344  * end_month() - XML element end function
1345  * "ldml dates calendars calendar months monthContext monthWidth month"

1368  assert (ld->data_buf_count < LOC_DATA_MONTH_ABBR_SIZE);

1372  strcpy (ld->month_names_abbreviated[ld->curr_period], ld->data_buffer);

1375  {

1379  }

1385  strcpy (ld->month_names_wide[ld->curr_period], ld->data_buffer);
1386  }

1397

1399  return 0;
1400 }

1667 {

1669  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
1670 
1671  assert (data != NULL);
1672 
1673  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
1674 
1675  /* number symbol is exactly one character (ASCII compatible) */
1676  if (ld->data_buf_count == 1 && (*(ld->data_buffer) >= ' ' && (unsigned char) *(ld->data_buffer) < 0x80))
1677  {
1678  if (strcmp (el_name, "decimal") == 0)
1679  {
1680  ld->number_decimal_sym = *(ld->data_buffer);

1682  else

1685  }
1686  }
1687  else
1688  {
1689  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "Invalid numeric symbol", -1);
1690  return -1;
1691  }
1692 
1693  clear_data_buffer ((XML_PARSER_DATA *) data);
1694 
1695  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "", 0);
1696  return 0;
1697 }

1719 
1720  /* all setting are optional */
1721  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "type", &att_val) == 0)
1722  {
1723  /* Type attribute found, store it. */
1724  if (strlen (att_val) != LOC_DATA_CURRENCY_ISO_CODE_LEN)
1725  {
1726  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "Currency ISO code invalid, " "it must be 3 chars long.", -1);
1727  return -1;
1728  }
1729  if (ld->default_currency_code != DB_CURRENCY_NULL)
1730  {
1731  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "Currency ISO code already set.", -1);
1732  return -1;
1733  }
1734  if (!intl_is_currency_symbol (att_val, &(ld->default_currency_code), &currency_size, CURRENCY_CHECK_MODE_ISO))
1735  {
1736  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "Currency ISO code not supported", -1);
1737  return -1;
1738  }
1739  }
1740  else
1741  {
1742  /* If <currency> does not have a type attribute, parsing fails. */
1743  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "Currency tag does not have an ISO code type " "attribute.", -1);
1744  return -1;
1745  }
1746 
1747  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "", 0);
1748  return 0;
1749 }
1750 
1751 
1752 /* LDML collation */
1753 /*
1754  * start_collations() - XML element start function
1755  * "ldml collations"
1756  *
1757  * return: 0 validation OK enter this element , 1 validation NOK do not enter
1758  * -1 error abort parsing
1759  * data: user data
1760  * attr: attribute/value pair array
1761  */
1762 static int
1763 start_collations (void *data, const char **attr)
1764 {
1765  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
1766  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
1767  char *valid_locales = NULL;
1768  int check_loc_len;
1769  char *t_start;
1770  char *t_end;
1771  char *att_val_end;
1772  bool locale_found = false;
1773  bool search_end = false;
1774 
1775  assert (data != NULL);
1776 
1777  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
1778 
1779  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "validSubLocales", &valid_locales) != 0)
1780  {
1781  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "", 1);
1782  return 1;
1783  }
1784 
1785  assert (ld->locale_name != NULL);
1786 
1787  check_loc_len = strlen (ld->locale_name);
1788  att_val_end = valid_locales + strlen (valid_locales);
1789 
1790  /* separate the locales_name into tokens */
1791  t_start = t_end = valid_locales;
1792 
1793  do
1794  {
1795  if (*t_end == '\0' || char_isspace ((int) *t_end))
1796  {
1797  /* token ended, check locale name */
1798  if ((t_end - t_start == 3 && memcmp (t_start, "all", 3) == 0) || (t_end - t_start == 1 && *t_start == '*')
1799  || (t_end - t_start == check_loc_len && memcmp (ld->locale_name, t_start, t_end - t_start) == 0))
1800  {
1801  locale_found = true;
1802  break;
1803  }
1804 
1805  if (*t_end == '\0')
1806  {
1807  search_end = true;
1808  }
1809 
1810  t_end++;
1811  t_start = t_end;
1812  }
1813  else
1814  {
1815  t_end++;
1816  }
1817  }
1818  while (!search_end);
1819 
1820  if (!locale_found)
1821  {
1822  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "", 1);
1823  return 1;
1824  }
1825 
1826  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "", 0);
1827  return 0;
1828 }
1829

1831  * start_one_collation() - XML element start function

1875  locale_coll->tail_coll.ldml_context.line_no = XML_GetCurrentLineNumber (pd->xml_parser);

1905 /*
1906  * start_collation_settings() - XML element start function
1907  * "ldml collations collation settings"
1908  *
1909  * return: 0 validation OK enter this element , 1 validation NOK do not enter
1910  * -1 error abort parsing
1911  * data: user data
1912  * attr: attribute/value pair array
1913  */
1914 static int
1915 start_collation_settings (void *data, const char **attr)
1916 {
1917  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
1918  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
1919  char *att_val = NULL;
1920  char err_msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE + PATH_MAX];
1921  COLL_TAILORING *curr_coll_tail = NULL;
1922 
1923  assert (data != NULL);
1924 
1925  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
1926  curr_coll_tail = LOC_CURRENT_COLL_TAIL (ld);
1927 
1928  att_val = NULL;
1929  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "id", &att_val) == 0)
1930  {
1931  assert (att_val != NULL);
1932  curr_coll_tail->coll_id = atoi (att_val);
1933 
1934  if (curr_coll_tail->coll_id < LANG_MAX_BUILTIN_COLLATIONS || curr_coll_tail->coll_id >= LANG_MAX_COLLATIONS)
1935  {
1936  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg) - 1,
1937  "File %s, line: %lu : " "Invalid collation numeric identifier : %d"
1938  " for collation '%s'. Valid range is from %d to %d", ld->ldml_context.ldml_file,
1939  XML_GetCurrentLineNumber (pd->xml_parser), curr_coll_tail->coll_id, curr_coll_tail->coll_name,
1940  LANG_MAX_BUILTIN_COLLATIONS, LANG_MAX_COLLATIONS - 1);
1941  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (err_msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
1942  return -1;
1943  }
1944  }
1945 
1946  att_val = NULL;
1947  /* all setting are optional */
1948  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "strength", &att_val) == 0)
1949  {
1950  T_LEVEL coll_strength = TAILOR_QUATERNARY;
1951  if (strcasecmp (att_val, "primary") == 0 || strcmp (att_val, "1") == 0)
1952  {
1953  coll_strength = TAILOR_PRIMARY;
1954  }
1955  else if ((strcasecmp (att_val, "secondary") == 0) || (strcmp (att_val, "2") == 0))
1956  {
1957  coll_strength = TAILOR_SECONDARY;
1958  }
1959  else if ((strcasecmp (att_val, "tertiary") == 0) || (strcmp (att_val, "3") == 0))
1960  {
1961  coll_strength = TAILOR_TERTIARY;
1962  }
1963  else if ((strcasecmp (att_val, "quaternary") == 0) || (strcmp (att_val, "4") == 0))
1964  {
1965  coll_strength = TAILOR_QUATERNARY;
1966  }
1967  else if ((strcasecmp (att_val, "identical") == 0) || (strcmp (att_val, "5") == 0))
1968  {
1969  coll_strength = TAILOR_IDENTITY;
1970  }
1971  else
1972  {
1973  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg) - 1,
1974  "File %s, line: %lu : " "Invalid collation strength : '%s'" " for collation '%s'",
1975  ld->ldml_context.ldml_file, XML_GetCurrentLineNumber (pd->xml_parser), att_val,
1976  curr_coll_tail->coll_name);
1977  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (err_msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
1978  return -1;
1979  }
1980 
1981  curr_coll_tail->uca_opt.sett_strength = coll_strength;
1982  }
1983 
1984  att_val = NULL;
1985 
1986  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "backwards", &att_val) == 0)
1987  {
1988  if (strcasecmp (att_val, "on") == 0)
1989  {
1990  curr_coll_tail->uca_opt.sett_backwards = true;
1991  }
1992  }
1993 
1994  att_val = NULL;
1995 
1996  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "caseLevel", &att_val) == 0)
1997  {
1998  if (strcasecmp (att_val, "on") == 0)
1999  {
2000  curr_coll_tail->uca_opt.sett_caseLevel = true;
2001  }
2002  }
2003 
2004  att_val = NULL;
2005 
2006  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "caseFirst", &att_val) == 0)
2007  {
2008  if (strcasecmp (att_val, "off") == 0)
2009  {
2010  curr_coll_tail->uca_opt.sett_caseFirst = 0;
2011  }
2012  else if (strcasecmp (att_val, "upper") == 0)
2013  {
2014  curr_coll_tail->uca_opt.sett_caseFirst = 1;
2015  }
2016  else if (strcasecmp (att_val, "lower") == 0)
2017  {
2018  curr_coll_tail->uca_opt.sett_caseFirst = 2;
2019  }
2020  }
2021 
2022  /* CUBRID specific collation settings */
2023  att_val = NULL;
2024  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "CUBRIDMaxWeights", &att_val) == 0)
2025  {
2026  assert (att_val != NULL);
2027  curr_coll_tail->sett_max_cp = atoi (att_val);
2028  }
2029 
2030  att_val = NULL;
2031  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "DUCETContractions", &att_val) == 0)
2032  {
2033  assert (att_val != NULL);
2034  if (strcasecmp (att_val, "use") == 0)
2035  {
2036  curr_coll_tail->uca_opt.sett_contr_policy |= CONTR_DUCET_USE;
2037  }
2038  }
2039 
2040  att_val = NULL;
2041  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "TailoringContractions", &att_val) == 0)
2042  {
2043  assert (att_val != NULL);
2044  if (strcasecmp (att_val, "use") == 0)
2045  {
2046  curr_coll_tail->uca_opt.sett_contr_policy |= CONTR_TAILORING_USE;
2047  }
2048  }
2049 
2050  att_val = NULL;
2051  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "CUBRIDExpansions", &att_val) == 0)
2052  {
2053  assert (att_val != NULL);
2054  if (strcasecmp (att_val, "use") == 0)
2055  {
2056  curr_coll_tail->uca_opt.sett_expansions = true;
2057  }
2058  }
2059 
2060  att_val = NULL;
2061  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "MatchContractionBoundary", &att_val) == 0)
2062  {
2063  assert (att_val != NULL);
2064  if (strcasecmp (att_val, "true") == 0)
2065  {
2066  curr_coll_tail->uca_opt.sett_match_contr = MATCH_CONTR_BOUND_ALLOW;
2067  }
2068  }
2069 
2070  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "", 0);
2071  return 0;
2072 }

2351  CUBRID_TAILOR_RULE *ct_rule = NULL;
2352  COLL_TAILORING *curr_coll_tail = NULL;

2385  ct_rule->end_cp_buf_type = BUF_TYPE_CODE;

2510 /*
2511  * handle_data_collation_rule() - XML element data content handle function
2512  * "ldml collations collation rules p"
2513  *
2514  * return: 0 handling OK, non-zero if handling NOK and stop parsing
2515  * (data): user data
2516  * (s): content buffer
2517  * (len): length of buffer
2518  */
2519 static int
2520 handle_data_collation_rule (void *data, const char *s, int len)
2521 {
2522  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
2523  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
2524  TAILOR_RULE *t_rule = NULL;
2525  COLL_TAILORING *curr_coll_tail = NULL;
2526 
2527  assert (data != NULL);
2528 
2529  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
2530  curr_coll_tail = LOC_CURRENT_COLL_TAIL (ld);
2531 
2532  assert (len >= 0);
2533 
2534  t_rule = &(curr_coll_tail->rules[curr_coll_tail->count_rules]);
2535  t_rule->t_buf = (char *) realloc (t_rule->t_buf, t_rule->t_buf_size + len);
2536  if (t_rule->t_buf == NULL)
2537  {
2538  pd->xml_error = XML_CUB_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
2539  PRINT_DEBUG_DATA (data, "memory allocation failed", -1);
2540  return -1;
2541  }
2542 
2543  /* copy partial data to data buffer */
2544  memcpy (t_rule->t_buf + t_rule->t_buf_size, s, len);
2545  t_rule->t_buf_size += len;
2546 
2547  if (pd->verbose)
2548  {
2549  char msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE];
2550 
2551  if (len < 32 && len < ERR_MSG_SIZE)
2552  {
2553  memcpy (msg, s, len);
2554  msg[len] = '\0';
2555  }
2556  else
2557  {
2558  char msg2[33];
2559 
2560  memcpy (msg2, s, 32);
2561  msg2[32] = '\0';
2562  snprintf (msg, sizeof (msg) - 1, "%s | %d bytes", msg2, len);
2563  }
2564  PRINT_DEBUG_DATA (data, msg, 0);
2565  }
2566 
2567  return 0;
2568 }

2570 /*
2571  * end_collation_rule() - XML element end function
2572  * "ldml collations collation rules p"
2573  *
2574  * return: 0 parser OK, non-zero value if parser NOK and stop parsing
2575  * data: user data
2576  * el_name: element name
2577  */
2578 static int
2579 end_collation_rule (void *data, const char *el_name)
2580 {
2581  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
2582  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
2583  TAILOR_RULE *t_rule = NULL;
2584  COLL_TAILORING *curr_coll_tail = NULL;
2585  int rule_id;
2586  int status;
2587 
2588  assert (data != NULL);
2589 
2590  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
2591  curr_coll_tail = LOC_CURRENT_COLL_TAIL (ld);
2592 
2593  /* rule finished, increase count */
2594  rule_id = curr_coll_tail->count_rules++;
2595  t_rule = &(curr_coll_tail->rules[rule_id]);
2596 
2597  if (strcmp (el_name, "p") == 0)
2598  {
2599  t_rule->level = TAILOR_PRIMARY;
2600  }
2601  else if (strcmp (el_name, "s") == 0)
2602  {
2603  t_rule->level = TAILOR_SECONDARY;
2604  }
2605  else if (strcmp (el_name, "t") == 0)
2606  {
2607  t_rule->level = TAILOR_TERTIARY;
2608  }
2609  else if (strcmp (el_name, "i") == 0)
2610  {
2611  t_rule->level = TAILOR_IDENTITY;
2612  }
2613  else if (strcmp (el_name, "pc") == 0)
2614  {
2615  t_rule->level = TAILOR_PRIMARY;
2616  t_rule->multiple_chars = true;
2617  }
2618  else if (strcmp (el_name, "sc") == 0)
2619  {
2620  t_rule->level = TAILOR_SECONDARY;
2621  t_rule->multiple_chars = true;
2622  }
2623  else if (strcmp (el_name, "tc") == 0)
2624  {
2625  t_rule->level = TAILOR_TERTIARY;
2626  t_rule->multiple_chars = true;
2627  }
2628  else if (strcmp (el_name, "ic") == 0)
2629  {
2630  t_rule->level = TAILOR_IDENTITY;
2631  t_rule->multiple_chars = true;
2632  }
2633  else
2634  {
2635  assert (false);
2636  pd->xml_error = XML_CUB_ERR_PARSER;
2637  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "Invalid element name", -1);
2638  return -1;
2639  }
2640 
2641  status = common_collation_end_rule (data, ld, rule_id, t_rule);
2642  if (status != 0)
2643  {
2644  return status;
2645  }
2646 
2647  return 0;
2648 }

2650 /*
2651  * start_collation_x() - XML element start function
2652  * "ldml collations collation rules x"
2653  *
2654  * return: 0 validation OK enter this element , 1 validation NOK do not enter
2655  * -1 error abort parsing
2656  * data: user data
2657  * attr: attribute/value pair array
2658  */
2659 static int
2660 start_collation_x (void *data, const char **attr)
2661 {
2662  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
2663  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
2664  TAILOR_RULE *t_rule = NULL;
2665  int status;
2666

2668 
2669  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
2670 
2671  t_rule = new_collation_rule (ld);
2672 
2673  if (t_rule == NULL)
2674  {
2675  pd->xml_error = XML_CUB_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
2676  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "memory allocation failed", -1);
2677  return -1;
2678  }
2679 
2680  if (ld->last_rule_pos_type != RULE_POS_BUFFER)
2681  {
2682  pd->xml_error = XML_CUB_ERR_PARSER;
2683  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "Last <reset> tag is invalid", -1);
2684  return -1;
2685  }

2688  if (status != 0)
2689  {
2690  return status;
2691  }
2692 
2693  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "", 0);
2694  return 0;
2695 }

3033  * data: user data

3202 /*
3203  * end_transform_buffer() - XML element end function
3204  * "ldml alphabets alphabet u s"
3205  *
3206  * return: 0 parser OK, non-zero value if parser NOK and stop parsing
3207  * data: user data
3208  * el_name: element name
3209  */
3210 static int
3211 end_transform_buffer (void *data, const char *el_name)
3212 {
3213  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
3214  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
3215  TRANSFORM_RULE *tf_rule = NULL;
3216  char *tf_buf = NULL;
3217 
3218  assert (data != NULL);
3219 
3220  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
3221 
3222  assert (ld->alpha_tailoring.count_rules < ld->alpha_tailoring.max_rules);
3223  tf_rule = &(ld->alpha_tailoring.rules[ld->alpha_tailoring.count_rules]);
3224 
3225  if (ld->data_buf_count <= 0)
3226  {
3227  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "Expecting non-empty string", -1);
3228  pd->xml_error = XML_CUB_ERR_PARSER;
3229  goto error_exit;
3230  }
3231 
3232  tf_buf = (char *) malloc (ld->data_buf_count);
3233  if (tf_buf == NULL)
3234  {
3235  pd->xml_error = XML_CUB_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
3236  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "memory allocation failed", -1);
3237  goto error_exit;
3238  }
3239 
3240  memcpy (tf_buf, ld->data_buffer, ld->data_buf_count);
3241 
3242  assert (tf_rule->type == TR_LOWER || tf_rule->type == TR_UPPER);
3243 
3244  if (strcmp (el_name, "s") == 0)
3245  {
3246  if (tf_rule->src != NULL || tf_rule->src_size != 0)
3247  {
3248  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "duplicate source for case rule", -1);
3249  pd->xml_error = XML_CUB_ERR_PARSER;
3250  goto error_exit;
3251  }
3252 
3253  tf_rule->src = tf_buf;
3254  tf_rule->src_size = ld->data_buf_count;
3255  }
3256  else if (strcmp (el_name, "d") == 0)
3257  {
3258  if (tf_rule->dest != NULL || tf_rule->dest_size != 0)
3259  {
3260  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "duplicate destination for case rule", -1);
3261  pd->xml_error = XML_CUB_ERR_PARSER;
3262  goto error_exit;
3263  }
3264 
3265  tf_rule->dest = tf_buf;
3266  tf_rule->dest_size = ld->data_buf_count;
3267  }
3268  else
3269  {
3270  assert (false);
3271  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "Internal LDML parser error", -1);
3272  pd->xml_error = XML_CUB_ERR_PARSER;
3273  goto error_exit;
3274  }
3275 
3276  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "", 0);
3277 
3278  clear_data_buffer ((XML_PARSER_DATA *) data);
3279 
3280  return 0;
3281 
3282 error_exit:
3283 
3284  clear_data_buffer ((XML_PARSER_DATA *) data);
3285 
3286  return -1;
3287 }

3389 /* General LDML handling functions */
3390 /*
3391  * handle_data() - XML element data content handle function
3392  * generic data handling function
3393  *
3394  * return: 0 handling OK, non-zero if handling NOK and stop parsing
3395  * (data): user data
3396  * (s): content buffer
3397  * (len): length of buffer
3398  */
3399 static int
3400 handle_data (void *data, const char *s, int len)
3401 {
3402  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
3403  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
3404  char msg[64];
3405 
3406  assert (data != NULL);
3407 
3408  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
3409 
3410  assert (len >= 0);
3411 
3412  if (ld->data_buf_count + len >= LOC_DATA_BUFF_SIZE)
3413  {
3414  pd->xml_error = XML_CUB_ERR_PARSER;
3415  sprintf (msg, "Too much data : %d + %d bytes", ld->data_buf_count, len);
3416  PRINT_DEBUG_DATA (data, msg, -1);
3417  return -1;
3418  }
3419 
3420  /* copy partial data to data buffer */
3421  memcpy (ld->data_buffer + ld->data_buf_count, s, len);
3422  ld->data_buf_count += len;
3423  ld->data_buffer[ld->data_buf_count] = '\0';
3424 
3425  if (pd->verbose)
3426  {
3427  char msg[64];
3428 
3429  if (len < 64)
3430  {
3431  memcpy (msg, s, len);
3432  msg[len] = '\0';
3433  }
3434  else
3435  {
3436  char msg2[33];
3437 
3438  memcpy (msg2, s, 32);
3439  msg2[32] = '\0';
3440  sprintf (msg, "%s | %d bytes", msg2, len);
3441  }
3442  PRINT_DEBUG_DATA (data, msg, 0);
3443  }
3444 
3445  return 0;
3446 }

3460 
3461  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
3462 
3463  ld->data_buf_count = 0;
3464  *(ld->data_buffer) = '\0';
3465 }

3497 /*

3499  *
3500  * return: rule
3501  * ld(in): locale data
3502  */
3503 static TAILOR_RULE *
3504 new_collation_rule (LOCALE_DATA * ld)
3505 {
3506  TAILOR_RULE *t_rule = NULL;
3507  COLL_TAILORING *curr_coll_tail = NULL;
3508 
3509  assert (ld != NULL);
3510 
3511  curr_coll_tail = LOC_CURRENT_COLL_TAIL (ld);
3512

3514  if (curr_coll_tail->count_rules + 1 >= curr_coll_tail->max_rules)
3515  {
3516  curr_coll_tail->rules = (TAILOR_RULE *)
3517  realloc (curr_coll_tail->rules,
3518  sizeof (TAILOR_RULE) * (curr_coll_tail->max_rules + LOC_DATA_TAILOR_RULES_COUNT_GROW));
3519

3521  {
3522  return NULL;
3523  }
3524 
3525  curr_coll_tail->max_rules += LOC_DATA_TAILOR_RULES_COUNT_GROW;
3526  }
3527 
3528  /* will use slot indicated by 'coll->count_rules' */
3529  t_rule = &(curr_coll_tail->rules[curr_coll_tail->count_rules]);
3530  memset (t_rule, 0, sizeof (TAILOR_RULE));
3531 
3532  return t_rule;
3533 }

3600  /* will use slot indicated by 'coll->cub_count_rules' */
3601  ct_rule = &(curr_coll_tail->cub_rules[curr_coll_tail->cub_count_rules]);
3602  memset (ct_rule, 0, sizeof (CUBRID_TAILOR_RULE));
3603 
3604  return ct_rule;
3605 }

3607 /*
3608  * print_debug_start_el() - print debug info for start of XML element
3609  *
3610  * return:
3611  * data(in):
3612  * attrs(in):
3613  * status(in): status returned from start function
3614  */
3615 static void
3616 print_debug_start_el (void *data, const char **attrs, const char *msg, const int status)
3617 {
3618  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
3619  const char **curr_att;
3620 
3621  assert (data != NULL);
3622  assert (attrs != NULL);
3623 
3624  if (pd->verbose)
3625  {
3626  int i;
3627 
3628  assert (pd->ce != NULL);
3629  assert (pd->ce->def != NULL);
3630 
3631  for (i = 0; i < pd->ce->def->depth; i++)
3632  {
3633  printf (" ");
3634  }
3635  printf ("<%s", pd->ce->short_name);
3636 
3637  for (curr_att = attrs; *curr_att != NULL; curr_att++, curr_att++)
3638  {
3639  printf (" %s=\"%s\"", curr_att[0], curr_att[1]);
3640  }
3641 
3642  if (*msg == '\0' && status == 0)
3643  {
3644  printf (">\n");
3645  }
3646  else
3647  {
3648  printf ("> " XML_COMMENT_START " %s ", msg);
3649 
3650  if (status == 0)
3651  {
3652  printf (XML_COMMENT_END "\n");
3653  }
3654  else if (status == -1)
3655  {
3656  printf (" * NOK, Aborting ! *" XML_COMMENT_END "\n");
3657  }
3658  else
3659  {
3660  printf (" * Ignore *" XML_COMMENT_END "\n");
3661  }
3662  }
3663  }
3664 }

3753 /*
3754  * locale_alloc_collation_id() - allocates collation id
3755  *
3756  * return:
3757  *
3758  * Note : Ranges of collation id:
3759  * 0 - 31(*) : built-in collations (32)
3760  * 32(*) - 46 : generic collations (language independent) (15)
3761  * 47 - 255 : language dependent collations (208 = 26 * 8)
3762  * Collation is name is in format: charset_lang_desc1_desc2_..
3763  * utf8_de_exp : Collation specific to de (German) with expansions
3764  * utf8_gen_ai_ci : Generic collation, accent and case insensitive
3765  *
3766  */
3767 static void
3768 locale_alloc_collation_id (COLL_TAILORING * coll_tail)
3769 {
3770 #define ID_PER_RANGE 8
3771 #define START_GENERIC_RANGE LANG_MAX_BUILTIN_COLLATIONS
3772 #define START_LANG_RANGE 47
3773 
3774  int coll_id = 0;
3775  char coll_name[COLL_NAME_SIZE];
3776  const char *charset_part, *lang_part, *desc_part;
3777  int range_start, range_size;
3778 
3779  strcpy (coll_name, coll_tail->coll_name);
3780 
3781  charset_part = coll_name;
3782  lang_part = strchr (coll_name, '_');
3783  if (lang_part != NULL)
3784  {
3785  lang_part++;
3786  desc_part = strchr (lang_part, '_');
3787  if (desc_part != NULL)
3788  {
3789  desc_part++;
3790  }
3791  }
3792  else
3793  {
3794  desc_part = NULL;
3795  }
3796 
3797  if (lang_part != NULL)
3798  {
3799  if (strncasecmp (lang_part, "gen", 3) == 0)
3800  {
3801  range_start = START_GENERIC_RANGE;
3802  range_size = (START_LANG_RANGE - START_GENERIC_RANGE) + 1;
3803  }
3804  else
3805  {
3806  int s = (int) *lang_part;
3807  s = (char_isupper (s)) ? (s + ('a' - 'A')) : s;
3808  s = (s > 'z') ? 'z' : ((s < 'a') ? 'a' : s);
3809  s -= 'a';
3810  range_start = START_LANG_RANGE + s * ID_PER_RANGE;
3811  range_size = ID_PER_RANGE;
3812  }
3813 
3814  if (desc_part != NULL)
3815  {
3816  while (desc_part < coll_name + strlen (coll_name))
3817  {
3818  coll_id += *desc_part++;
3819  }
3820  }
3821 
3822  coll_id %= range_size;
3823  coll_id += range_start;
3824  }
3825 
3826  coll_tail->coll_id = coll_id;
3827 
3828 #undef ID_PER_RANGE
3829 #undef START_GENERIC_RANGE
3830 #undef START_LANG_RANGE
3831 }
3832 
3833 /*
3834  * locale_check_collation_id() - checks a collation id
3835  *
3836  * return:
3837  *
3838  *
3839  */
3840 static int
3841 locale_check_collation_id (const COLL_TAILORING * coll_tail)
3842 {
3843  char err_msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE];
3844  static int taken_collations[LANG_MAX_COLLATIONS] = { 0 };
3845 
3846  assert (coll_tail->coll_id >= LANG_MAX_BUILTIN_COLLATIONS && coll_tail->coll_id < LANG_MAX_COLLATIONS);
3847 
3848  if (taken_collations[coll_tail->coll_id] != 0)
3849  {
3850  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg) - 1,
3851  "Invalid collation numeric identifier : %d" " for collation '%s'. Id is already taken.",
3852  coll_tail->coll_id, coll_tail->coll_name);
3853  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (err_msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
3854  return ER_LOC_GEN;
3855  }
3856 
3857  taken_collations[coll_tail->coll_id] = 1;
3858  return NO_ERROR;
3859 }

3861 /*
3862  * load_console_conv_data() - Loads the console conversion file (standardised
3863  * and availabe at Unicode.org).
3864  * Returns: error code
3865  * ld(in/out) : locale data
3866  * is_verbose(in) :
3867  */
3868 static int
3869 load_console_conv_data (LOCALE_DATA * ld, bool is_verbose)
3870 {
3871  TXT_CONV_ITEM *txt_conv_array = NULL;
3872  FILE *fp = NULL;
3873  char *end_p;
3874  char err_msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE];
3875  char str[TXT_CONV_LINE_SIZE];
3876  char conv_file_name[PATH_MAX];
3877  int status = NO_ERROR;
3878  int line_count = 0;
3879  int txt_conv_max_items = 0;
3880  int txt_conv_count_items = 0;
3881  unsigned int i;
3882  unsigned int cp_text = 0;
3883  unsigned int cp_unicode = 0;
3884  TXT_CONV_ITEM min_values = { 0xffff, 0xffff };
3885  TXT_CONV_ITEM max_values = { 0, 0 };
3886 
3887  assert (ld != NULL);
3888 
3889  if (ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_NO_CONVERSION)
3890  {
3891  if (is_verbose)
3892  {
3893  printf ("No console conversion data\n");
3894  }
3895  return status;
3896  }
3897 
3898  if (ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_ISO_88591_BUILTIN
3899  || ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_ISO_88599_BUILTIN)
3900  {
3901  if (is_verbose)
3902  {
3903  printf ("Built-in console conversion\n");
3904  }
3905  ld->txt_conv.conv_type = ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_type;
3906  return status;
3907  }
3908 
3909  strncpy (conv_file_name, ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_file, sizeof (conv_file_name) - 1);
3910  conv_file_name[sizeof (conv_file_name) - 1] = '\0';
3911 
3912  fp = fopen_ex (conv_file_name, "rt");
3913  if (fp == NULL)
3914  {
3915  envvar_codepagedir_file (conv_file_name, sizeof (conv_file_name), ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_file);
3916  fp = fopen_ex (conv_file_name, "rt");
3917  }
3918 
3919  if (fp == NULL)
3920  {
3921  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg) - 1, "Cannot open file %s", ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_file);
3922  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (err_msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
3923  status = ER_LOC_GEN;
3924  goto error;
3925  }
3926 
3927  if (is_verbose)
3928  {
3929  printf ("Using file: %s\n", conv_file_name);
3930  }
3931 
3932  memset (ld->txt_conv.byte_flag, 0, sizeof (ld->txt_conv.byte_flag));
3933  while (fgets (str, sizeof (str), fp))
3934  {
3935  char *s;
3936 
3937  line_count++;
3938 
3939  s = str;
3940  /* skip white spaces */
3941  while (char_isspace (*s))
3942  {
3943  s++;
3944  }
3945 
3946  if (*s == '\0' || *s == '#')
3947  {
3948  continue;
3949  }
3950 
3951  str_to_uint32 (&cp_text, &end_p, s, 16);
3952 
3953  /* skip codepoints values above 0xFFFF */
3954  if (cp_text > 0xffff || (cp_text > 0xff && ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE))
3955  {
3956  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg) - 1, "Codepoint value too big" " in file :%s at line %d",
3957  ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_file, line_count);
3958  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (err_msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
3959  status = ER_LOC_GEN;
3960  goto error;
3961  }
3962 
3963  /* skip first token */
3964  while (!char_isspace (*s))
3965  {
3966  s++;
3967  }
3968  /* skip white spaces */
3969  while (char_isspace (*s))
3970  {
3971  s++;
3972  }
3973 
3974  if (*s == '\0' || *s == '#')
3975  {
3976  if (ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_2BYTE)
3977  {
3978  assert (cp_text <= 0xff);
3979  if (strncasecmp (s, "#DBCS", 5) == 0)
3980  {
3981  ld->txt_conv.byte_flag[cp_text] = 1;
3982  }
3983  else
3984  {
3985  ld->txt_conv.byte_flag[cp_text] = 2;
3986  }
3987  }
3988  continue;
3989  }
3990 
3991  str_to_uint32 (&cp_unicode, &end_p, s, 16);
3992 
3993  /* first codepoints which maps the same character are not included */
3994  if (((ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE && cp_text < 0x80)
3995  || ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_2BYTE) && (cp_text == cp_unicode
3996  && min_values.text_cp == 0xffff
3997  && min_values.unicode_cp == 0xffff))
3998  {
3999  continue;
4000  }
4001 
4002  if (cp_unicode > 0xffff)
4003  {
4004  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg) - 1, "Codepoint value too big" " in file :%s at line %d",
4005  ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_file, line_count);
4006  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (err_msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
4007  status = ER_LOC_GEN;
4008  goto error;
4009  }
4010 
4011  if (txt_conv_count_items >= txt_conv_max_items)
4012  {
4013  txt_conv_array =
4014  (TXT_CONV_ITEM *) realloc (txt_conv_array,
4015  sizeof (TXT_CONV_ITEM) * (txt_conv_max_items + TXT_CONV_ITEM_GROW_COUNT));
4016 
4017  if (txt_conv_array == NULL)
4018  {
4019  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
4020  status = ER_LOC_GEN;
4021  goto error;
4022  }
4023 
4024  txt_conv_max_items += TXT_CONV_ITEM_GROW_COUNT;
4025  }
4026 
4027  txt_conv_array[txt_conv_count_items].text_cp = cp_text;
4028  txt_conv_array[txt_conv_count_items].unicode_cp = cp_unicode;
4029 
4030  min_values.text_cp = MIN (min_values.text_cp, cp_text);
4031  min_values.unicode_cp = MIN (min_values.unicode_cp, cp_unicode);
4032 
4033  max_values.text_cp = MAX (max_values.text_cp, cp_text);
4034  max_values.unicode_cp = MAX (max_values.unicode_cp, cp_unicode);
4035 
4036  txt_conv_count_items++;
4037  }
4038 
4039  if (is_verbose)
4040  {
4041  printf ("Building %d console conversion rules\n", txt_conv_count_items);
4042  }
4043 
4044  /* build conversions */
4045  ld->txt_conv.text_first_cp = min_values.text_cp;
4046  ld->txt_conv.text_last_cp = max_values.text_cp;
4047 
4048  ld->txt_conv.utf8_first_cp = min_values.unicode_cp;
4049  ld->txt_conv.utf8_last_cp = max_values.unicode_cp;
4050 
4051  assert (ld->txt_conv.text_first_cp < ld->txt_conv.text_last_cp);
4052  assert (ld->txt_conv.utf8_first_cp < ld->txt_conv.utf8_last_cp);
4053 
4054  if (ld->txt_conv.text_last_cp == 0 || ld->txt_conv.utf8_last_cp == 0)
4055  {
4056  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("Invalid console mapping", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
4057  status = ER_LOC_GEN;
4058  goto error;
4059  }
4060 
4061  ld->txt_conv.text_to_utf8 =
4062  (CONV_CP_TO_BYTES *) malloc (sizeof (CONV_CP_TO_BYTES) *
4063  (ld->txt_conv.text_last_cp - ld->txt_conv.text_first_cp + 1));
4064  memset (ld->txt_conv.text_to_utf8, 0,
4065  sizeof (CONV_CP_TO_BYTES) * (ld->txt_conv.text_last_cp - ld->txt_conv.text_first_cp + 1));
4066 
4067  ld->txt_conv.utf8_to_text =
4068  (CONV_CP_TO_BYTES *) malloc (sizeof (CONV_CP_TO_BYTES) *
4069  (ld->txt_conv.utf8_last_cp - ld->txt_conv.utf8_first_cp + 1));
4070  memset (ld->txt_conv.utf8_to_text, 0,
4071  sizeof (CONV_CP_TO_BYTES) * (ld->txt_conv.utf8_last_cp - ld->txt_conv.utf8_first_cp + 1));
4072 
4073  if (ld->txt_conv.text_to_utf8 == NULL || ld->txt_conv.utf8_to_text == NULL)
4074  {
4075  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
4076  status = ER_LOC_GEN;
4077  goto error;
4078  }
4079 
4080  for (i = 0; i < ld->txt_conv.text_last_cp - ld->txt_conv.text_first_cp + 1; i++)
4081  {
4082  ld->txt_conv.text_to_utf8[i].size = 1;
4083  *(ld->txt_conv.text_to_utf8[i].bytes) = '?';
4084  }
4085 
4086  for (i = 0; i < ld->txt_conv.utf8_last_cp - ld->txt_conv.utf8_first_cp + 1; i++)
4087  {
4088  ld->txt_conv.utf8_to_text[i].size = 1;
4089  *(ld->txt_conv.utf8_to_text[i].bytes) = '?';
4090  }
4091 
4092  for (i = 0; (int) i < txt_conv_count_items; i++)
4093  {
4094  CONV_CP_TO_BYTES *text_to_utf8_item = NULL;
4095  CONV_CP_TO_BYTES *utf8_to_text_item = NULL;
4096 
4097  cp_text = txt_conv_array[i].text_cp;
4098  cp_unicode = txt_conv_array[i].unicode_cp;
4099 
4100  assert (cp_text >= ld->txt_conv.text_first_cp && cp_text <= ld->txt_conv.text_last_cp);
4101 
4102  assert (cp_unicode >= ld->txt_conv.utf8_first_cp && cp_unicode <= ld->txt_conv.utf8_last_cp);
4103 
4104  text_to_utf8_item = &(ld->txt_conv.text_to_utf8[cp_text - ld->txt_conv.text_first_cp]);
4105  utf8_to_text_item = &(ld->txt_conv.utf8_to_text[cp_unicode - ld->txt_conv.utf8_first_cp]);
4106 
4107  text_to_utf8_item->size = intl_cp_to_utf8 (cp_unicode, text_to_utf8_item->bytes);
4108 
4109  if (ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE)
4110  {
4111  utf8_to_text_item->size = 1;
4112  utf8_to_text_item->bytes[0] = cp_text;
4113  }
4114  else
4115  {
4116  assert (ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_2BYTE);
4117  utf8_to_text_item->size = intl_cp_to_dbcs (cp_text, ld->txt_conv.byte_flag, utf8_to_text_item->bytes);
4118  }
4119  }
4120 
4121  assert (fp != NULL);
4122  fclose (fp);
4123 
4124  assert (txt_conv_array != NULL);
4125  free (txt_conv_array);
4126 
4127  ld->txt_conv.conv_type = ld->txt_conv_prm.conv_type;
4128  ld->txt_conv.win_codepages = strdup (ld->txt_conv_prm.win_codepages);
4129  ld->txt_conv.nl_lang_str = strdup (ld->txt_conv_prm.nl_lang_str);
4130  if (ld->txt_conv.nl_lang_str == NULL)
4131  {
4132  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
4133  status = ER_LOC_GEN;
4134  goto error;
4135  }
4136 
4137  return status;
4138 
4139 error:
4140 
4141  if (fp != NULL)
4142  {
4143  fclose (fp);
4144  }
4145 
4146  if (txt_conv_array != NULL)
4147  {
4148  free (txt_conv_array);
4149  }
4150 
4151  return status;
4152 }
4153 
4154 /*
4155  * comp_func_parse_order_index - compare function for sorting parse order
4156  * indexes for month and weekday names, based on the reversed
4157  * binary order of the LDML tokens
4158  *
4159  * Note: this function is used by the genlocale tool
4160  * The elements in the arrays should be NUL-terminated strings, stored
4161  * in fixed length char arrays. Encoding is not relevant, the purpose
4162  * of this comparison is to make sure that the tokenizer first tries
4163  * to match some tokens before others which can be prefixes for them.
4164  * E.g. In Vietnamese(vi_VN), the October translation followed by
4165  * a space is a prefix for the translations of November and December.
4166  */
4167 static int
4168 comp_func_parse_order_index (const void *arg1, const void *arg2)
4169 {
4170  char *s1;
4171  char *s2;
4172  char pos1;
4173  char pos2;
4174  int cmp;
4175 
4176  pos1 = *((char *) arg1);
4177  pos2 = *((char *) arg2);
4178  s1 = (char *) (cmp_token_name_array + pos1 * cmp_token_name_size);
4179  s2 = (char *) (cmp_token_name_array + pos2 * cmp_token_name_size);
4180 
4181  cmp = strcmp (s2, s1);
4182 
4183  return (cmp == 0) ? (pos1 - pos2) : cmp;
4184 }
4185 
4186 /*
4187  * locale_make_calendar_parse_order() - computes the order in which the
4188  * string tokenizer should search for matches with
4189  * weekday and month names, both wide and abbreviated.
4190  *
4191  * return:
4192  * ld(in/out): LOCALE_DATA for which to do the processing
4193  */
4194 static void
4195 locale_make_calendar_parse_order (LOCALE_DATA * ld)
4196 {
4197  int i;
4198  for (i = 0; i < CAL_MONTH_COUNT; i++)
4199  {
4200  ld->month_names_abbr_parse_order[i] = i;
4201  ld->month_names_wide_parse_order[i] = i;
4202  }
4203  for (i = 0; i < CAL_DAY_COUNT; i++)
4204  {
4205  ld->day_names_abbr_parse_order[i] = i;
4206  ld->day_names_wide_parse_order[i] = i;
4207  }
4208  for (i = 0; i < CAL_AM_PM_COUNT; i++)
4209  {
4210  ld->am_pm_parse_order[i] = i;
4211  }
4212 
4213  cmp_token_name_array = (char *) (ld->month_names_abbreviated);
4214  cmp_token_name_size = LOC_DATA_MONTH_ABBR_SIZE;
4215  qsort (ld->month_names_abbr_parse_order, CAL_MONTH_COUNT, sizeof (char), comp_func_parse_order_index);
4216 
4217  cmp_token_name_array = (char *) (ld->month_names_wide);
4218  cmp_token_name_size = LOC_DATA_MONTH_WIDE_SIZE;
4219  qsort (ld->month_names_wide_parse_order, CAL_MONTH_COUNT, sizeof (char), comp_func_parse_order_index);
4220 
4221  cmp_token_name_array = (char *) (ld->day_names_abbreviated);
4222  cmp_token_name_size = LOC_DATA_DAY_ABBR_SIZE;
4223  qsort (ld->day_names_abbr_parse_order, CAL_DAY_COUNT, sizeof (char), comp_func_parse_order_index);
4224 
4225  cmp_token_name_array = (char *) (ld->day_names_wide);
4226  cmp_token_name_size = LOC_DATA_DAY_WIDE_SIZE;
4227  qsort (ld->day_names_wide_parse_order, CAL_DAY_COUNT, sizeof (char), comp_func_parse_order_index);
4228 
4229  cmp_token_name_array = (char *) (ld->am_pm);
4230  cmp_token_name_size = LOC_DATA_AM_PM_SIZE;
4231  qsort (ld->am_pm_parse_order, CAL_AM_PM_COUNT, sizeof (char), comp_func_parse_order_index);
4232 }

4234 /*
4235  * locale_init_data() - initializes one locale data
4236  *
4237  * return:
4238  * ld(in/out):
4239  * locale_name(in):
4240  */
4241 void
4242 locale_init_data (LOCALE_DATA * ld, const char *locale_name)
4243 {
4244  memset (ld, 0, sizeof (LOCALE_DATA));
4245  ld->curr_period = -1;
4246 
4247  assert (strlen (locale_name) < (int) sizeof (ld->locale_name));
4248  strcpy (ld->locale_name, locale_name);
4249 
4250  /* default number symbols */
4251  ld->number_decimal_sym = ',';
4252  ld->number_group_sym = '.';
4253  ld->default_currency_code = DB_CURRENCY_NULL;
4254 
4255  ld->alpha_tailoring.sett_max_letters = -1;
4256 }

4258 /*
4259  * locale_destroy_data() - frees memory allocated for one locale data
4260  *
4261  * return:
4262  * ld(in/out):
4263  */
4264 void
4265 locale_destroy_data (LOCALE_DATA * ld)
4266 {
4267  int i;
4268 
4269  assert (ld != NULL);
4270 
4271  /* collations */
4272  for (i = 0; i < ld->coll_cnt; i++)
4273  {
4274  locale_destroy_collation_data (&(ld->collations[i].opt_coll));
4275  locale_destroy_collation_tailorings (&(ld->collations[i].tail_coll));
4276  }
4277 
4278  free (ld->collations);
4279  ld->collations = NULL;
4280  ld->coll_cnt = 0;
4281 
4282  /* alphabet tailoring */
4283  locale_destroy_alphabet_tailoring (&(ld->alpha_tailoring));
4284 
4285  /* alphabets */
4286  locale_destroy_alphabet_data (&(ld->alphabet));
4287  locale_destroy_alphabet_data (&(ld->identif_alphabet));
4288 
4289  locale_destroy_console_conversion (&(ld->txt_conv));
4290 
4291  locale_destroy_normalization_data (&(ld->unicode_normalization));
4292 
4293  /* ldml context file path */
4294  if (ld->ldml_context.ldml_file != NULL)
4295  {
4296  free (ld->ldml_context.ldml_file);
4297  }
4298 }
4299 
4300 /*
4301  * locale_destroy_alphabet_data() - frees memory for one locale alphabet
4302  * return:
4303  * a(in/out):
4304  *
4305  * Note : Alphabets that are common are not freed
4306  */
4307 void
4308 locale_destroy_alphabet_data (const ALPHABET_DATA * a)
4309 {
4310  assert (a != NULL);
4311 
4312  if (a->lower_cp != NULL)
4313  {
4314  free (a->lower_cp);
4315  }
4316 
4317  if (a->upper_cp != NULL)
4318  {
4319  free (a->upper_cp);
4320  }
4321 
4322  memset ((void *) a, 0, sizeof (ALPHABET_DATA));
4323 }

4325 /*
4326  * locale_destroy_collation_tailorings() - frees memory for one locale
4327  * collation tailorings
4328  * return:
4329  * ct(in/out):
4330  */
4331 static void
4332 locale_destroy_collation_tailorings (const COLL_TAILORING * ct)
4333 {
4334  int i;
4335 
4336  assert (ct != NULL);
4337 
4338  /* collation tailorings */
4339  for (i = 0; i < ct->count_rules; i++)
4340  {
4341  TAILOR_RULE *t_rule = &(ct->rules[i]);
4342 
4343  assert (t_rule != NULL);
4344  assert (t_rule->t_buf != NULL);
4345 
4346  if (t_rule->t_buf != NULL)
4347  {
4348  assert (t_rule->t_buf_size > 0);
4349  free (t_rule->t_buf);
4350  }
4351 
4352  if (t_rule->r_buf != NULL)
4353  {
4354  assert (t_rule->r_buf_size > 0);
4355  free (t_rule->r_buf);
4356  }
4357 
4358  memset (t_rule, 0, sizeof (TAILOR_RULE));
4359  }
4360 
4361  if (ct->rules != NULL)
4362  {
4363  assert (ct->max_rules > 0);
4364  free (ct->rules);
4365  }
4366 
4367  if (ct->cub_rules != NULL)
4368  {
4369  assert (ct->cub_max_rules > 0);
4370  free (ct->cub_rules);
4371  }
4372 
4373  if (ct->ldml_context.ldml_file != NULL)
4374  {
4375  free (ct->ldml_context.ldml_file);
4376  }
4377 
4378  memset ((void *) ct, 0, sizeof (COLL_TAILORING));
4379 }

4381 /*
4382  * locale_destroy_collation_data() - frees memory for collation data
4383  * return:
4384  * cd(in/out):
4385  */
4386 static void
4387 locale_destroy_collation_data (const COLL_DATA * cd)

4390 
4391  /* collation data */

4393  {
4394  free (cd->weights);
4395  }
4396 
4397  if (cd->next_cp != NULL)
4398  {
4399  free (cd->next_cp);
4400  }
4401 
4402  /* contractions */
4403  if (cd->uca_num != NULL)
4404  {
4405  free (cd->uca_num);
4406  }
4407 
4408  if (cd->uca_w_l13 != NULL)
4409  {
4410  free (cd->uca_w_l13);
4411  }
4412 
4413  if (cd->uca_w_l4 != NULL)
4414  {
4415  free (cd->uca_w_l4);
4416  }

4418  if (cd->cp_first_contr_array != NULL)
4419  {
4420  free (cd->cp_first_contr_array);
4421  }
4422 
4423  if (cd->contr_list != NULL)
4424  {
4425  free (cd->contr_list);
4426  }
4427 
4428  memset ((void *) cd, 0, sizeof (COLL_DATA));
4429 }

4431 /*
4432  * locale_destroy_alphabet_tailoring() - frees memory for alphabet tailorings
4433  * return:
4434  * at(in/out):
4435  */
4436 static void
4437 locale_destroy_alphabet_tailoring (const ALPHABET_TAILORING * at)
4438 {
4439  int i;
4440 
4441  assert (at != 0);
4442 
4443  /* case tailoring */
4444  for (i = 0; i < at->count_rules; i++)
4445  {
4446  TRANSFORM_RULE *tf_rule = &(at->rules[i]);
4447 
4448  assert (tf_rule != NULL);
4449  assert (tf_rule->src != NULL);
4450  assert (tf_rule->dest != NULL);
4451 
4452  if (tf_rule->src != NULL)
4453  {
4454  assert (tf_rule->src_size > 0);
4455  free (tf_rule->src);
4456  }
4457 
4458  if (tf_rule->dest != NULL)
4459  {
4460  assert (tf_rule->dest_size > 0);
4461  free (tf_rule->dest);
4462  }
4463 
4464  memset (tf_rule, 0, sizeof (TRANSFORM_RULE));
4465  }
4466 
4467  if (at->rules != NULL)
4468  {
4469  assert (at->max_rules > 0);
4470  free (at->rules);
4471  }
4472 
4473  if (at->ldml_context.ldml_file != NULL)
4474  {
4475  free (at->ldml_context.ldml_file);
4476  }
4477 
4478  memset ((void *) at, 0, sizeof (ALPHABET_TAILORING));
4479 }

4500  }

4502  if (tc->text_to_utf8 != NULL)

4515 /*
4516  * locale_compile_locale() - process locale data loaded from LDML file(s)
4517  *
4518  * return: error code
4519  * lf(in): structure containing file paths
4520  * ld(in): locale data to be processed
4521  * is_verbose(in):
4522  */
4523 int
4524 locale_compile_locale (LOCALE_FILE * lf, LOCALE_DATA * ld, bool is_verbose)
4525 {
4526  XML_PARSER_DATA ldml_parser;
4527  LOC_SHARED_DATA *norm_sh_entry = NULL;
4528  char *locale_str = NULL;
4529  int er_status = NO_ERROR;
4530  int i;
4531 
4532  assert (lf != NULL);
4533  locale_str = lf->locale_name;
4534 
4535  if (is_verbose)
4536  {
4537  printf ("\n*** Parsing LDML\n");
4538  }
4539 
4540  locale_init_data (ld, locale_str);
4541  ldml_parser.ud = ld;
4542  ldml_parser.verbose = is_verbose;
4543 
4544  ld->ldml_context.ldml_file = strdup (lf->ldml_file);
4545  ld->ldml_context.line_no = 1;
4546 
4547  ldml_parser.xml_parser =
4548  xml_init_parser (&ldml_parser, lf->ldml_file, "UTF-8", ldml_elements,
4549  sizeof (ldml_elements) / sizeof (XML_ELEMENT_DEF *));
4550 
4551  if (ldml_parser.xml_parser == NULL)
4552  {
4553  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("Cannot init XML parser", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
4554 
4555  er_status = ER_LOC_GEN;
4556  goto exit;
4557  }
4558 
4559  xml_parser_exec (&ldml_parser);
4560 
4561  if (ldml_parser.xml_error == XML_CUB_NO_ERROR)
4562  {
4563  if (is_verbose)
4564  {
4565  printf ("Parsing finished.\n");
4566  printf ("Date format: %s\n", ld->dateFormat);
4567  printf ("Time format: %s\n", ld->timeFormat);
4568  printf ("Datetime format: %s\n", ld->datetimeFormat);
4569  printf ("Timestamp format: %s\n", ld->timestampFormat);
4570  printf ("Timetz format: %s\n", ld->timetzFormat);
4571  printf ("Datetimetz format: %s\n", ld->datetimetzFormat);
4572  printf ("Timestamptz format: %s\n", ld->timestamptzFormat);
4573  }
4574  }
4575  else
4576  {
4577  char msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE];
4578  const char *xml_err_text = (char *) XML_ErrorString (XML_GetErrorCode (ldml_parser.xml_parser));
4579 
4580  snprintf (msg, sizeof (msg) - 1, "Error parsing file %s, " "line : %d, column : %d. Internal XML: %s",
4581  ldml_parser.filepath, ldml_parser.xml_error_line, ldml_parser.xml_error_column, xml_err_text);
4582 
4583  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
4584  er_status = ER_LOC_GEN;
4585  goto exit;
4586  }
4587 
4588  locale_make_calendar_parse_order (ld);
4589 
4590  if (ld->alpha_tailoring.sett_max_letters == -1)
4591  {
4592  ld->alpha_tailoring.sett_max_letters = MAX_UNICODE_CHARS;
4593  }
4594 
4595  if (is_verbose)
4596  {
4597  printf ("\n*** Processing alphabet ***\nNumber of letters = %d\n", ld->alpha_tailoring.sett_max_letters);
4598  }
4599 
4600  if (ld->alpha_tailoring.sett_max_letters == 0)
4601  {
4602  ld->alphabet.l_count = ld->alpha_tailoring.sett_max_letters;
4603  }
4604  else
4605  {
4606  LOC_SHARED_DATA *alphabet_sh_entry = NULL;
4607  LDML_CONTEXT *ldml_context = &(ld->alpha_tailoring.ldml_context);
4608 
4609  er_status = unicode_process_alphabet (ld, is_verbose);
4610  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
4611  {
4612  goto exit;
4613  }
4614 
4615  if (ld->alphabet.a_type == ALPHABET_UNICODE)
4616  {
4617  er_status =
4618  locale_check_and_set_shared_data (LOC_SHARED_ALPHABET, "unicode", NULL, ldml_context, &alphabet_sh_entry);
4619  }
4620  else if (ld->alphabet.a_type == ALPHABET_ASCII)
4621  {
4622  er_status =
4623  locale_check_and_set_shared_data (LOC_SHARED_ALPHABET, "ascii", NULL, ldml_context, &alphabet_sh_entry);
4624  }
4625 
4626  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
4627  {
4628  goto exit;
4629  }
4630 
4631  ld->alphabet.do_not_save = (alphabet_sh_entry != NULL) ? true : false;
4632 
4633  alphabet_sh_entry = NULL;
4634  if (ld->identif_alphabet.a_type == ALPHABET_UNICODE)
4635  {
4636  er_status =
4637  locale_check_and_set_shared_data (LOC_SHARED_ALPHABET, "unicode", NULL, ldml_context, &alphabet_sh_entry);
4638  }
4639  else if (ld->identif_alphabet.a_type == ALPHABET_ASCII)
4640  {
4641  er_status =
4642  locale_check_and_set_shared_data (LOC_SHARED_ALPHABET, "ascii", NULL, ldml_context, &alphabet_sh_entry);
4643  }
4644 
4645  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
4646  {
4647  goto exit;
4648  }
4649 
4650  ld->identif_alphabet.do_not_save = (alphabet_sh_entry != NULL) ? true : false;
4651  if (ld->identif_alphabet.do_not_save == false)
4652  {
4653  /* check that casing data matches the rule of INTL_IDENTIFIER_CASING_SIZE_MULTIPLIER: the ratio between the
4654  * size in bytes of lower (or upper) case character (or sequence of characters) and the size in bytes of
4655  * original character is less than INTL_IDENTIFIER_CASING_SIZE_MULTIPLIER */
4656  unsigned int cp;
4657  ALPHABET_DATA *a = &(ld->identif_alphabet);
4658  unsigned char dummy[INTL_UTF8_MAX_CHAR_SIZE];
4659 
4660  for (cp = 0; (int) cp < a->l_count; cp++)
4661  {
4662  int case_cnt, case_size, cp_size;
4663  unsigned int *lower_cp = &(a->lower_cp[cp * a->lower_multiplier]);
4664  unsigned int *upper_cp = &(a->upper_cp[cp * a->upper_multiplier]);
4665 
4666  for (case_size = 0, case_cnt = 0; case_cnt < a->lower_multiplier && *lower_cp != 0;
4667  case_cnt++, lower_cp++)
4668  {
4669  if (*lower_cp == cp)
4670  {
4671  /* character does not have lower case */
4672  case_size = 0;
4673  break;
4674  }
4675  case_size += intl_cp_to_utf8 (*lower_cp, dummy);
4676  }
4677 
4678  if (case_size > 0)
4679  {
4680  cp_size = intl_cp_to_utf8 (cp, dummy);
4681  if (case_size > cp_size * INTL_IDENTIFIER_CASING_SIZE_MULTIPLIER)
4682  {
4683  char msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE];
4684 
4685  snprintf (msg, sizeof (msg) - 1,
4686  "Lower case " "sequence for codepoint Ux%04X is too "
4687  "big: %d bytes; expecting at most %d", cp, case_size,
4688  cp_size * INTL_IDENTIFIER_CASING_SIZE_MULTIPLIER);
4689  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
4690  er_status = ER_LOC_GEN;
4691  goto exit;
4692  }
4693  }
4694 
4695  for (case_size = 0, case_cnt = 0; case_cnt < a->upper_multiplier && *upper_cp != 0;
4696  case_cnt++, upper_cp++)
4697  {
4698  if (*upper_cp == cp)
4699  {
4700  /* character does not have upper case */
4701  case_size = 0;
4702  break;
4703  }
4704  case_size += intl_cp_to_utf8 (*upper_cp, dummy);
4705  }
4706 
4707  if (case_size > 0)
4708  {
4709  cp_size = intl_cp_to_utf8 (cp, dummy);
4710  if (case_size > cp_size * INTL_IDENTIFIER_CASING_SIZE_MULTIPLIER)
4711  {
4712  char msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE];
4713 
4714  snprintf (msg, sizeof (msg) - 1,
4715  "Upper case " "sequence for codepoint Ux%04X is too "
4716  "big: %d bytes; expecting at most %d", cp, case_size,
4717  cp_size * INTL_IDENTIFIER_CASING_SIZE_MULTIPLIER);
4718  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
4719  er_status = ER_LOC_GEN;
4720  goto exit;
4721  }
4722  }
4723  }
4724  }
4725  }
4726 
4727  if (is_verbose)
4728  {
4729  printf ("\n*** Processing Unicode normalization data ***\n");
4730  }
4731 
4732  er_status = locale_check_and_set_shared_data (LOC_SHARED_NORMALIZATION, "normalization", NULL, NULL, &norm_sh_entry);
4733 
4734  ld->unicode_normalization.do_not_save = (norm_sh_entry != NULL) ? true : false;
4735 
4736  if (norm_sh_entry == NULL)
4737  {
4738  /* not shared, process normalization */
4739  er_status = unicode_process_normalization (ld, is_verbose);
4740  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
4741  {
4742  goto exit;
4743  }
4744  }
4745 
4746  if (is_verbose)
4747  {
4748  printf ("\n*** Processing console conversion data ***\n");
4749  }
4750 
4751  er_status = load_console_conv_data (ld, is_verbose);
4752  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
4753  {
4754  goto exit;
4755  }
4756 
4757  if (ld->coll_cnt == 0 && is_verbose)
4758  {
4759  printf ("\n*** No collation defined ***\n");
4760  }
4761 
4762  for (i = 0; i < ld->coll_cnt; i++)
4763  {
4764  LOC_SHARED_DATA *coll_sh_entry = NULL;
4765  LOCALE_COLLATION *lc = &(ld->collations[i]);
4766  char shared_coll_data[COLL_SHARED_DATA_SIZE];
4767 
4768 
4769  strncpy (lc->opt_coll.coll_name, lc->tail_coll.coll_name, COLL_NAME_SIZE);
4770  lc->opt_coll.coll_name[COLL_NAME_SIZE - 1] = '\0';
4771 
4772  if (!lang_is_coll_name_allowed (lc->opt_coll.coll_name))
4773  {
4774  char msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE];
4775 
4776  snprintf (msg, sizeof (msg) - 1,
4777  "Collation name %s " "not allowed. It cannot contain white-spaces "
4778  "or have same name as a built-in collation", lc->opt_coll.coll_name);
4779 
4780  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
4781  er_status = ER_LOC_GEN;
4782  goto exit;
4783  }
4784 
4785  snprintf (shared_coll_data, sizeof (shared_coll_data) - 1, "%d", lc->tail_coll.coll_id);
4786 
4787  er_status =
4788  locale_check_and_set_shared_data (LOC_SHARED_COLLATION, lc->tail_coll.coll_name, &shared_coll_data,
4789  &(lc->tail_coll.ldml_context), &coll_sh_entry);
4790  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
4791  {
4792  goto exit;
4793  }
4794 
4795  lc->do_not_save = (coll_sh_entry != NULL) ? true : false;
4796 
4797  if (coll_sh_entry != NULL)
4798  {
4799  /* check found entry */
4800  const char *coll_sh_data = (const char *) coll_sh_entry->data;
4801 
4802  assert (coll_sh_data != NULL);
4803 
4804  if (strcmp (shared_coll_data, coll_sh_data) != 0)
4805  {
4806  /* found collation with same name buf different collation shared data (collation id) */
4807  char msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE + 2 * PATH_MAX];
4808 
4809  snprintf (msg, sizeof (msg) - 1,
4810  "File: %s, line: %d : " "collation name %s (id:%d) already defined in "
4811  "file: %s, line: %d with id: %s", lc->tail_coll.ldml_context.ldml_file,
4812  lc->tail_coll.ldml_context.line_no, lc->tail_coll.coll_name, lc->tail_coll.coll_id,
4813  coll_sh_entry->ldml_context.ldml_file, coll_sh_entry->ldml_context.line_no, coll_sh_data);
4814 
4815  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
4816  er_status = ER_LOC_GEN;
4817  goto exit;
4818  }
4819  else if (strcmp (lc->tail_coll.ldml_context.ldml_file, coll_sh_entry->ldml_context.ldml_file) != 0
4820  || lc->tail_coll.ldml_context.line_no != coll_sh_entry->ldml_context.line_no)
4821  {
4822  /* same collation, just put an debug info */
4823  printf ("Warning : Definition of collation %s (id: %d) " "ignored in file: %s, line: %d. "
4824  "Using the definition from file: %s, line: %d.\n", lc->tail_coll.coll_name, lc->tail_coll.coll_id,
4825  lc->tail_coll.ldml_context.ldml_file, lc->tail_coll.ldml_context.line_no,
4826  coll_sh_entry->ldml_context.ldml_file, coll_sh_entry->ldml_context.line_no);
4827  }
4828 
4829  continue;
4830  }
4831 
4832  if (lc->tail_coll.sett_max_cp == -1)
4833  {
4834  lc->tail_coll.sett_max_cp = MAX_UNICODE_CHARS;
4835  }
4836 
4837  if (is_verbose)
4838  {
4839  printf ("\n*** Processing collation : %s ***\n" "Number of weights = %d\n", lc->tail_coll.coll_name,
4840  lc->tail_coll.sett_max_cp);
4841  }
4842 
4843  if (lc->tail_coll.sett_max_cp == 0)
4844  {
4845  lc->opt_coll.w_count = lc->tail_coll.sett_max_cp;
4846  }
4847  else
4848  {
4849  er_status = uca_process_collation (lc, is_verbose);
4850  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
4851  {
4852  goto exit;
4853  }
4854 
4855  if (lc->tail_coll.coll_id <= 0)
4856  {
4857  locale_alloc_collation_id (&lc->tail_coll);
4858  }
4859 
4860  er_status = locale_check_collation_id (&lc->tail_coll);
4861  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
4862  {
4863  goto exit;
4864  }
4865  lc->opt_coll.coll_id = lc->tail_coll.coll_id;
4866  }
4867 
4868  er_status = locale_compute_coll_checksum (&(lc->opt_coll));
4869  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
4870  {
4871  goto exit;
4872  }
4873  if (is_verbose)
4874  {
4875  printf ("ID : %d | Checksum : %s\n", lc->opt_coll.coll_id, lc->opt_coll.checksum);
4876  }
4877  }
4878 
4879  er_status = locale_compute_locale_checksum (ld);
4880  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
4881  {
4882  goto exit;
4883  }
4884 
4885  if (is_verbose)
4886  {
4887  printf ("\n Locale checksum :%s\n", ld->checksum);
4888  }
4889 
4890 exit:
4891  xml_destroy_parser (&ldml_parser);
4892  uca_free_data ();
4893  unicode_free_data ();
4894 
4895  if (is_verbose)
4896  {
4897  printf ("\n\nLocale finished\n\n\n");
4898  }
4899 
4900  return er_status;
4901 }
4902 
4903 /*
4904  * locale_mark_duplicate_collations - finds duplicate arrays within all
4905  * collations and uses string identifiers from
4906  * LOCALE_DATA structure to mark the arrays which will
4907  * not be exported to the shared library, but another
4908  * identical array will be loaded instead.
4909  *
4910  * return: error status
4911  *
4912  * ld(in): all locale data loaded from LDML and compiled
4913  * start_index(in): index of the first working locale (in ld)
4914  * end_index(in): index of the last working locale stored in the ld array
4915  */
4916 void
4917 locale_mark_duplicate_collations (LOCALE_DATA ** ld, int start_index, int end_index, bool is_verbose)
4918 {
4919 #define PRINT_DUPLICATE_SYMBOL_NAME(symbol, dupl_coll, orig_coll, do_print) \
4920  if (do_print) \
4921  { \
4922  printf ("\n *** Duplicate array: %s in collation %s is a duplicate " \
4923  "of %s from collation %s", (symbol), \
4924  (dupl_coll)->opt_coll.coll_name, \
4925  (symbol), (orig_coll)->opt_coll.coll_name); \
4926  }
4927 
4928  int i1, i2, j1, j2;
4929  LOCALE_COLLATION *cur_coll, *comp_coll;
4930  LOCALE_DATA *cur_ld, *comp_ld;
4931 
4932  /* Search for duplicate arrays. In order to avoid errors, search must be done backwards for the cursor collation,
4933  * while searching forward in the locales; the rule of determining the identifier to be stored is that the first
4934  * occurence is considered as the original, and all identical arrays that follow are duplicates */
4935  for (i1 = end_index - 1; i1 >= start_index; i1--)
4936  {
4937  cur_ld = ld[i1];
4938  for (j1 = cur_ld->coll_cnt - 1; j1 >= 0; j1--)
4939  {
4940  cur_coll = &(cur_ld->collations[j1]);
4941 
4942  for (i2 = start_index; i2 <= i1; i2++)
4943  {
4944  comp_ld = ld[i2];
4945  for (j2 = 0; (i1 == i2 && j2 < j1) || (i1 > i2 && j2 < comp_ld->coll_cnt); j2++)
4946  {
4947  comp_coll = &(comp_ld->collations[j2]);
4948  /* Two COLL_INFO structures are refferenced.Compare them. */
4949 
4950  if (cur_coll->opt_coll.w_count != comp_coll->opt_coll.w_count)
4951  {
4952  continue;
4953  }
4954 
4955  if (cur_coll->opt_coll.uca_opt.sett_expansions == comp_coll->opt_coll.uca_opt.sett_expansions)
4956  {
4957  if (!cur_coll->opt_coll.uca_opt.sett_expansions)
4958  {
4959  if (*(cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_weights_ref) == '\0'
4960  && memcmp (cur_coll->opt_coll.weights, comp_coll->opt_coll.weights,
4961  sizeof (comp_coll->opt_coll.weights[0]) * cur_coll->opt_coll.w_count) == 0)
4962  {
4963  sprintf (cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_weights_ref, "%s_%s", "coll_weights",
4964  comp_coll->opt_coll.coll_name);
4965  PRINT_DUPLICATE_SYMBOL_NAME ("coll_weights", cur_coll, comp_coll, is_verbose);
4966  }
4967  }
4968  else
4969  {
4970  if (cur_coll->opt_coll.uca_exp_num != comp_coll->opt_coll.uca_exp_num)
4971  {
4972  continue;
4973  }
4974 
4975  if (*(cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_uca_num_ref) == '\0'
4976  && memcmp (cur_coll->opt_coll.uca_num, comp_coll->opt_coll.uca_num,
4977  sizeof (comp_coll->opt_coll.uca_num[0]) * comp_coll->opt_coll.w_count) == 0)
4978  {
4979  sprintf (cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_uca_num_ref, "%s_%s", "coll_uca_num",
4980  comp_coll->opt_coll.coll_name);
4981  PRINT_DUPLICATE_SYMBOL_NAME ("coll_uca_num", cur_coll, comp_coll, is_verbose);
4982  }
4983 
4984  if (*(cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_uca_w_l13_ref) == '\0'
4985  && memcmp (cur_coll->opt_coll.uca_w_l13, comp_coll->opt_coll.uca_w_l13,
4986  sizeof (UCA_L13_W) * cur_coll->opt_coll.uca_exp_num *
4987  cur_coll->opt_coll.w_count) == 0)
4988  {
4989  sprintf (cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_uca_w_l13_ref, "%s_%s", "coll_uca_w_l13",
4990  comp_coll->opt_coll.coll_name);
4991  PRINT_DUPLICATE_SYMBOL_NAME ("coll_uca_w_l13", cur_coll, comp_coll, is_verbose);
4992  }
4993  if (cur_coll->opt_coll.uca_opt.sett_strength >= TAILOR_QUATERNARY
4994  && comp_coll->opt_coll.uca_opt.sett_strength >= TAILOR_QUATERNARY
4995  && *(cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_uca_w_l4_ref) == '\0'
4996  && memcmp (cur_coll->opt_coll.uca_w_l4, comp_coll->opt_coll.uca_w_l4,
4997  sizeof (UCA_L4_W) * cur_coll->opt_coll.uca_exp_num *
4998  cur_coll->opt_coll.w_count) == 0)
4999  {
5000  sprintf (cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_uca_w_l4_ref, "%s_%s", "coll_uca_w_l4",
5001  comp_coll->opt_coll.coll_name);
5002  PRINT_DUPLICATE_SYMBOL_NAME ("coll_uca_w_l4", cur_coll, comp_coll, is_verbose);
5003  }
5004  }
5005  } /* endif equal sett_expansions */
5006 
5007  if (*(cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_next_cp_ref) == '\0'
5008  && memcmp (cur_coll->opt_coll.next_cp, comp_coll->opt_coll.next_cp,
5009  sizeof (comp_coll->opt_coll.next_cp[0]) * comp_coll->opt_coll.w_count) == 0)
5010  {
5011  sprintf (cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_next_cp_ref, "%s_%s", "coll_next_cp",
5012  comp_coll->opt_coll.coll_name);
5013  PRINT_DUPLICATE_SYMBOL_NAME ("coll_next_cp", cur_coll, comp_coll, is_verbose);
5014  }
5015 
5016  /* compare contraction data */
5017  if (cur_coll->opt_coll.count_contr > 0
5018  && cur_coll->opt_coll.count_contr == comp_coll->opt_coll.count_contr)
5019  {
5020  if (cur_coll->opt_coll.contr_min_size == comp_coll->opt_coll.contr_min_size
5021  && *(cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_contr_list_ref) == '\0'
5022  && memcmp (cur_coll->opt_coll.contr_list, comp_coll->opt_coll.contr_list,
5023  sizeof (COLL_CONTRACTION) * comp_coll->opt_coll.count_contr) == 0)
5024  {
5025  sprintf (cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_contr_list_ref, "%s_%s", "coll_contr_list",
5026  comp_coll->opt_coll.coll_name);
5027  PRINT_DUPLICATE_SYMBOL_NAME ("coll_contr_list", cur_coll, comp_coll, is_verbose);
5028  }
5029 
5030  if (cur_coll->opt_coll.cp_first_contr_offset == comp_coll->opt_coll.cp_first_contr_offset
5031  && cur_coll->opt_coll.cp_first_contr_count == comp_coll->opt_coll.cp_first_contr_count
5032  && *(cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_cp_first_contr_array_ref) == '\0'
5033  && memcmp (cur_coll->opt_coll.cp_first_contr_array, comp_coll->opt_coll.cp_first_contr_array,
5034  sizeof (comp_coll->opt_coll.cp_first_contr_array[0]) *
5035  comp_coll->opt_coll.w_count) == 0)
5036  {
5037  sprintf (cur_coll->coll_ref.coll_cp_first_contr_array_ref, "%s_%s",
5038  "coll_cp_first_contr_array", comp_coll->opt_coll.coll_name);
5039  PRINT_DUPLICATE_SYMBOL_NAME ("coll_cp_first_" "contr_array", cur_coll, comp_coll, is_verbose);
5040  }
5041  }
5042  }
5043  }
5044  }
5045  }
5046 #undef PRINT_DUPLICATE_SYMBOL_NAME
5047 }
5048 
5049 /*
5050  * locale_save_all_to_C_file - saves all locale data to C source file, for
5051  * later use when compiling them into a locale shared
5052  * library.
5053  *
5054  * return: error code
5055  * ld(in): locale data
5056  * start_index(in): starting index inside ld array for locales to export
5057  * loc_count(in): number of locales stored in the ld array
5058  * lf(in): locale file info
5059  */
5060 int
5061 locale_save_all_to_C_file (LOCALE_DATA ** ld, int start_index, int end_index, LOCALE_FILE * lf)
5062 {
5063  int er_status = NO_ERROR;
5064  int i;
5065 
5066  for (i = start_index; i < end_index; i++)
5067  {
5068  er_status = locale_save_to_C_file (lf[i], ld[i]);
5069  if (er_status != NO_ERROR)
5070  {
5071  break;
5072  }
5073  }
5074 
5075  return er_status;
5076 }

5078 /*
5079  * locale_get_cfg_locales() - reads the locale strings and file paths configured
5080  *
5081  * return: error code
5082  * locale_files(in/out):
5083  * p_num_locales(out): number of user defined locales
5084  * is_lang_init(in): true if this is called in context of lang initialization
5085  *
5086  * Note : This funtion is called in two contexts :
5087  * - language initialization (no error is set in this case)
5088  * - locale generation admin tool (error is generated)
5089  */
5090 int
5091 locale_get_cfg_locales (LOCALE_FILE ** p_locale_files, int *p_num_locales, bool is_lang_init)
5092 {
5093  char locale_cfg_file[PATH_MAX];
5094  char line[1024];
5095  FILE *fp = NULL;
5096  LOCALE_FILE *locale_files = NULL;
5097  int num_locales;
5098  int max_locales = 10;
5099  char msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE];
5100  int err_status = NO_ERROR;
5101 
5102  assert (p_locale_files != NULL);
5103  assert (p_num_locales != NULL);
5104 
5105  envvar_confdir_file (locale_cfg_file, sizeof (locale_cfg_file), "cubrid_locales.txt");
5106 
5107  fp = fopen_ex (locale_cfg_file, "rt");
5108  if (fp == NULL)
5109  {
5110  if (is_lang_init)
5111  {
5112  /* no error is recorded, 'cubrid_locales.txt' is optional */
5113  goto exit;
5114  }
5115  else
5116  {
5117  snprintf (msg, sizeof (msg) - 1, "Cannot open file %s", locale_cfg_file);
5118  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
5119  err_status = ER_LOC_GEN;
5120  goto exit;
5121  }
5122  }
5123 
5124  locale_files = NULL;
5125  num_locales = 0;
5126 
5127  locale_files = (LOCALE_FILE *) malloc (max_locales * sizeof (LOCALE_FILE));
5128  if (locale_files == NULL)
5129  {
5130  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", ER_LOC_INIT, true);
5131  err_status = ER_LOC_INIT;
5132  goto exit;
5133  }
5134 
5135  while (fgets (line, sizeof (line) - 1, fp) != NULL)
5136  {
5137  char *str, *next;
5138  LOCALE_FILE *loc;
5139 
5140  if (*line == '\0' || *line == '#' || char_isspace ((int) *line))
5141  {
5142  continue;
5143  }
5144 
5145  num_locales++;
5146 
5147  if (num_locales >= max_locales)
5148  {
5149  max_locales *= 2;
5150  locale_files = (LOCALE_FILE *) realloc (locale_files, max_locales * sizeof (LOCALE_FILE));
5151 
5152  if (locale_files == NULL)
5153  {
5154  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", ER_LOC_INIT, true);
5155  err_status = ER_LOC_INIT;
5156  goto exit;
5157  }
5158  }
5159 
5160  loc = &(locale_files[num_locales - 1]);
5161  memset (loc, 0, sizeof (LOCALE_FILE));
5162 
5163  str = line;
5164  err_status = str_pop_token (str, &(loc->locale_name), &next);
5165  if (err_status != NO_ERROR)
5166  {
5167  goto exit;
5168  }
5169 
5170  if (next == NULL)
5171  {
5172  continue;
5173  }
5174 
5175  str = next;
5176  err_status = str_pop_token (str, &(loc->ldml_file), &next);
5177  if (err_status != NO_ERROR)
5178  {
5179  goto exit;
5180  }
5181 
5182  if (next == NULL)
5183  {
5184  continue;
5185  }
5186 
5187  str = next;
5188  err_status = str_pop_token (str, &(loc->lib_file), &next);
5189  if (err_status != NO_ERROR)
5190  {
5191  goto exit;
5192  }
5193  }
5194 
5195  *p_locale_files = locale_files;
5196  *p_num_locales = num_locales;
5197 
5198 exit:
5199  if (fp != NULL)
5200  {
5201  fclose (fp);
5202  }
5203 
5204  return err_status;
5205 }
5206 
5207 /*
5208  * locale_check_and_set_default_files() - checks if the files for locale is set
5209  * if not set, the default file paths are
5210  * computed
5211  *
5212  * return:
5213  * lf(in/out):
5214  * is_lang_init(in): true if this is called in context of lang initialization
5215  *
5216  * Note : This funtion is called in two contexts :
5217  * - language initialization (no error is set in this case)
5218  * - locale generation admin tool (error is generated)
5219  */
5220 int
5221 locale_check_and_set_default_files (LOCALE_FILE * lf, bool is_lang_init)
5222 {
5223  bool is_alloc_ldml_file = false;
5224  bool is_alloc_lib_file = false;
5225  int er_status = NO_ERROR;
5226 
5227  assert (lf != NULL);
5228 
5229  if (lf->locale_name == NULL || strlen (lf->locale_name) > LOC_LOCALE_STR_SIZE)
5230  {
5231  er_status = is_lang_init ? ER_LOC_INIT : ER_LOC_GEN;
5232  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("invalid locale name in 'cubrid_locales.txt'", er_status, true);
5233  goto error;
5234  }
5235 
5236  if (lf->ldml_file == NULL || *(lf->ldml_file) == '\0' || *(lf->ldml_file) == '*')
5237  {
5238  /* generate name for LDML file */
5239  char ldml_short_file[LOC_LOCALE_STR_SIZE + 13];
5240 
5241  snprintf (ldml_short_file, sizeof (ldml_short_file) - 1, "cubrid_%s.xml", lf->locale_name);
5242  ldml_short_file[sizeof (ldml_short_file) - 1] = '\0';
5243 
5244  if (lf->ldml_file != NULL)
5245  {
5246  free (lf->ldml_file);
5247  }
5248 
5249  lf->ldml_file = (char *) malloc (PATH_MAX + 1);
5250  if (lf->ldml_file == NULL)
5251  {
5252  er_status = is_lang_init ? ER_LOC_INIT : ER_LOC_GEN;
5253  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", er_status, true);
5254  goto error;
5255  }
5256 
5257  is_alloc_ldml_file = true;
5258  envvar_ldmldir_file (lf->ldml_file, PATH_MAX, ldml_short_file);
5259  }
5260 
5261  if (lf->lib_file == NULL || *(lf->lib_file) == '\0' || *(lf->lib_file) == '*')
5262  {
5263  /* generate name for locale lib file */
5264  char lib_short_file[PATH_MAX];
5265 
5266  snprintf (lib_short_file, sizeof (lib_short_file) - 1, "libcubrid_%s.%s", lf->locale_name, LOCLIB_FILE_EXT);
5267  lib_short_file[sizeof (lib_short_file) - 1] = '\0';
5268 
5269  if (lf->lib_file != NULL)
5270  {
5271  free (lf->lib_file);
5272  }
5273 
5274  lf->lib_file = (char *) malloc (PATH_MAX + 1);
5275  if (lf->lib_file == NULL)
5276  {
5277  er_status = is_lang_init ? ER_LOC_INIT : ER_LOC_GEN;
5278  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", er_status, true);
5279  goto error;
5280  }
5281 
5282  is_alloc_lib_file = true;
5283  envvar_libdir_file (lf->lib_file, PATH_MAX, lib_short_file);
5284 
5285  if (is_lang_init)
5286  {
5287  FILE *fp;
5288 
5289  /* check that default lib file exists, otherwise switch to the common libray locale */
5290  fp = fopen_ex (lf->lib_file, "rb");
5291  if (fp == NULL)
5292  {
5293  snprintf (lib_short_file, sizeof (lib_short_file) - 1, "libcubrid_all_locales.%s", LOCLIB_FILE_EXT);
5294  lib_short_file[sizeof (lib_short_file) - 1] = '\0';
5295 
5296  assert (lf->lib_file != NULL);
5297 
5298  envvar_libdir_file (lf->lib_file, PATH_MAX, lib_short_file);
5299  }
5300  else
5301  {
5302  fclose (fp);
5303  }
5304  }
5305  }
5306 
5307  return NO_ERROR;
5308 
5309 error:
5310 
5311  if (is_alloc_ldml_file)
5312  {
5313  free (lf->ldml_file);
5314  lf->ldml_file = NULL;
5315  }
5316 
5317  if (is_alloc_lib_file)
5318  {
5319  free (lf->lib_file);
5320  lf->lib_file = NULL;
5321  }
5322  return er_status;
5323 }
5324 
5325 /*
5326  * save_contraction_to_C_file() - saves collation contraction data to C file
5327  *
5328  * return: zero if save is successful, non-zero otherwise
5329  * fp(in): file descriptor
5330  * c(in): contraction to save
5331  * use_expansion(in):
5332  * use_level_4(in):
5333  */
5334 static int
5335 save_contraction_to_C_file (FILE * fp, COLL_CONTRACTION * c, bool use_expansion, bool use_level_4)
5336 {
5337  assert (c != NULL);
5338  assert (fp != NULL);
5339 
5340  fprintf (fp, "\t{\n");
5341  fprintf (fp, "\t\t%u, \n", c->next);
5342  fprintf (fp, "\t\t%u, \n", c->wv);
5343 
5344  if (use_expansion)
5345  {
5346  assert (c->uca_num > 0 || c->uca_num <= MAX_UCA_EXP_CE);
5347 
5348  PRINT_UNNAMED_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "%uu", "\t\t", c->uca_num, c->uca_w_l13);
5349  fprintf (fp, ",\n");
5350 
5351  if (use_level_4)
5352  {
5353  PRINT_UNNAMED_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "%u", "\t\t", c->uca_num, c->uca_w_l4);
5354  }
5355  else
5356  {
5357  fprintf (fp, "\t\t{ 0 }");
5358  }
5359  }
5360  else
5361  {
5362  fprintf (fp, "\t\t{ 0 },\n\t\t{ 0 }");
5363  }
5364 
5365  fprintf (fp, ",\n\t\t");
5366  PRINT_STRING_TO_C_FILE (fp, c->c_buf, strlen (c->c_buf));
5367  fprintf (fp, ", \n");
5368  fprintf (fp, "\t\t%u, \n", c->cp_count);
5369  fprintf (fp, "\t\t%u, \n", c->size);
5370  fprintf (fp, "\t\t%u \n", c->uca_num);
5371 
5372  fprintf (fp, "} \n");
5373 
5374  return 0;
5375 }
