5377 /*
5378  * locale_prepare_C_file() - saves locale data to C source file, for
5379  * later use when generating the locale shared
5380  * library.
5381  *
5382  * return: error code
5383  * lf(in): locale file info
5384  * ld(in): locale data
5385  * c_file_path(in): the path to where to write the C file
5386  */
5387 int
5388 locale_prepare_C_file (void)
5389 {
5390  FILE *fp;
5391  char c_file_path[PATH_MAX];
5392  char err_msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE];
5393 
5394  envvar_loclib_dir_file (c_file_path, sizeof (c_file_path), "locale.c");
5395 
5396  fp = fopen_ex (c_file_path, "w");
5397  if (fp == NULL)
5398  {
5399  goto error;
5400  }
5401  fprintf (fp, "/* GENERATED FILE - DO NOT EDIT */\n");
5402 
5403 #if defined(WINDOWS)
5404  fprintf (fp, "#include <stdio.h>\n");
5405 #else
5406  fprintf (fp, "#include <stddef.h>\n");
5407 #endif
5408  fprintf (fp, "#include \"locale_lib_common.h\"\n\n");
5409  fclose (fp);
5410  return 0;
5411 error:
5412  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg) - 1, "Error opening file %s for rewrite.", c_file_path);
5413  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (err_msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
5414  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
5415 }
5416 
5417 /*
5418  * locale_save_to_C_file() - saves locale data to C source file, for
5419  * later use when generating the locale shared
5420  * library.
5421  *
5422  * return: error code
5423  * lf(in): locale file info
5424  * ld(in): locale data
5425  */
5426 static int
5427 locale_save_to_C_file (LOCALE_FILE lf, LOCALE_DATA * ld)
5428 {
5429  FILE *fp;
5430  char c_file_path[PATH_MAX];
5431  char err_msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE];
5432  int i;
5433 
5434  assert (ld != NULL);
5435 
5436  envvar_loclib_dir_file (c_file_path, sizeof (c_file_path), "locale.c");
5437 
5438  fp = fopen_ex (c_file_path, "a");
5439  if (fp == NULL)
5440  {
5441  goto error;
5442  }
5443  fprintf (fp, "/*\n * %s - generated from %s \n *\n */\n", ld->locale_name, lf.ldml_file);
5444 
5445  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "locale_name", ld->locale_name, ld->locale_name);
5446 
5447  locale_save_calendar_to_C_file (fp, ld);
5448 
5449  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "char", "number_decimal_sym", ld->number_decimal_sym, "'%c'", ld->locale_name);
5450  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "char", "number_group_sym", ld->number_group_sym, "'%c'", ld->locale_name);
5451  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "default_currency_code", ld->default_currency_code, "%d", ld->locale_name);
5452 
5453  locale_save_alphabets_to_C_file (fp, ld);
5454 
5455  /* number of collation associated with this locale */
5456  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "count_coll", ld->coll_cnt, "%d", ld->locale_name);
5457 
5458  for (i = 0; i < ld->coll_cnt; i++)
5459  {
5460  char coll_suffix[ERR_MSG_SIZE];
5461 
5462  /* Collation names are user defined: first save fixed name variables containing collations name included in the
5463  * LDML: collation_1_es_ES = "utf8_es_ES"; collation_2_es_ES = "utf8_es_ES_ci"; */
5464  snprintf (coll_suffix, sizeof (coll_suffix) - 1, "%d_%s", i, ld->locale_name);
5465  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "collation", ld->collations[i].opt_coll.coll_name, coll_suffix);
5466 
5467  if (ld->collations[i].do_not_save)
5468  {
5469  continue;
5470  }
5471 
5472  /* the collation data is decorated with the user defined name of the collation : coll_weights_utf8_es_ES = { ..
5473  * }; coll_weights_utf8_es_ES_ci = { .. }; */
5474  locale_save_collation_data_to_C_file (fp, &(ld->collations[i]));
5475  }
5476 
5477  locale_save_console_conv_to_C_file (fp, ld);
5478 
5479  locale_save_normalization_to_C_file (fp, ld);
5480 
5481  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "locale_checksum", ld->checksum, ld->locale_name);
5482 
5483  fclose (fp);
5484  return 0;
5485 
5486 error:
5487  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg) - 1, "Error opening file %s for append.", c_file_path);
5488  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (err_msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
5489  return ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
5490 }

5492 /*
5493  * locale_save_calendar_to_C_file() - saves calendar data to C source file,
5494  * as variables, for later use when generating the
5495  * locale shared library.
5496  *
5497  * return: error code
5498  * fp(in): file pointer where to write the data
5499  * ld(in): locale data
5500  */
5501 static int
5502 locale_save_calendar_to_C_file (FILE * fp, LOCALE_DATA * ld)
5503 {
5504  assert (ld != NULL);
5505  assert (fp != NULL);
5506 
5507  /* calendar format strings */
5508  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "date_format", ld->dateFormat, ld->locale_name);
5509  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "time_format", ld->timeFormat, ld->locale_name);
5510  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "datetime_format", ld->datetimeFormat, ld->locale_name);
5511  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "timestamp_format", ld->timestampFormat, ld->locale_name);
5512  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "timetz_format", ld->timetzFormat, ld->locale_name);
5513  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "datetimetz_format", ld->datetimetzFormat, ld->locale_name);
5514  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "timestamptz_format", ld->timestamptzFormat, ld->locale_name);
5515 
5516  /* calendar data arrays */
5517  PRINT_STRING_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "month_names_abbreviated", CAL_MONTH_COUNT, ld->month_names_abbreviated,
5518  ld->locale_name);
5519  PRINT_STRING_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "month_names_wide", CAL_MONTH_COUNT, ld->month_names_wide, ld->locale_name);
5520  PRINT_STRING_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "day_names_abbreviated", CAL_DAY_COUNT, ld->day_names_abbreviated, ld->locale_name);
5521  PRINT_STRING_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "day_names_wide", CAL_DAY_COUNT, ld->day_names_wide, ld->locale_name);
5522  PRINT_STRING_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "am_pm", CAL_AM_PM_COUNT, ld->am_pm, ld->locale_name);
5523 
5524  /* calendar parse order arrays */
5525  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "day_names_abbr_parse_order", "char", "%u", CAL_DAY_COUNT,
5526  ld->day_names_abbr_parse_order, ld->locale_name);
5527  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "day_names_wide_parse_order", "char", "%u", CAL_DAY_COUNT,
5528  ld->day_names_wide_parse_order, ld->locale_name);
5529  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "month_names_abbr_parse_order", "char", "%u", CAL_MONTH_COUNT,
5530  ld->month_names_abbr_parse_order, ld->locale_name);
5531  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "month_names_wide_parse_order", "char", "%u", CAL_MONTH_COUNT,
5532  ld->month_names_wide_parse_order, ld->locale_name);
5533  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "am_pm_parse_order", "char", "%u", CAL_AM_PM_COUNT, ld->am_pm_parse_order,
5534  ld->locale_name);
5535 
5536  return 0;
5537 }

5539 /*
5540  * locale_save_alphabets_to_C_file() - saves alphabet and identifier alphabet
5541  * to C source file as variables, for later use
5542  * when generating the locale shared library.
5543  *
5544  * return: error code
5545  * fp(in): file pointer where to write the data
5546  * a(in): alphabet data
5547  * save_w_identier_name(in): true if alphabet is to be saved as "identifier"
5548  * name
5549  * alpha_suffix(in): suffix to be applied to variables names
5550  */
5551 static int
5552 locale_save_one_alphabet_to_C_file (FILE * fp, ALPHABET_DATA * a, bool save_w_identier_name, const char *alpha_suffix)
5553 {
5554  assert (a != NULL);
5555  assert (fp != NULL);
5556 
5557  if (save_w_identier_name)
5558  {
5559  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "ident_alphabet_l_count", a->l_count, "%d", alpha_suffix);
5560 
5561  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "ident_alphabet_lower_multiplier", a->lower_multiplier, "%d", alpha_suffix);
5562  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "ident_alphabet_upper_multiplier", a->upper_multiplier, "%d", alpha_suffix);
5563  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "ident_alphabet_lower_cp", "unsigned int", "%u", a->l_count * a->lower_multiplier,
5564  a->lower_cp, alpha_suffix);
5565  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "ident_alphabet_upper_cp", "unsigned int", "%u", a->l_count * a->upper_multiplier,
5566  a->upper_cp, alpha_suffix);
5567  }
5568  else
5569  {
5570  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "alphabet_l_count", a->l_count, "%d", alpha_suffix);
5571  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "alphabet_lower_multiplier", a->lower_multiplier, "%d", alpha_suffix);
5572  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "alphabet_upper_multiplier", a->upper_multiplier, "%d", alpha_suffix);
5573  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "alphabet_lower_cp", "unsigned int", "%u", a->l_count * a->lower_multiplier,
5574  a->lower_cp, alpha_suffix);
5575  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "alphabet_upper_cp", "unsigned int", "%u", a->l_count * a->upper_multiplier,
5576  a->upper_cp, alpha_suffix);
5577  }
5578 
5579  return 0;
5580 }

5582 /*
5583  * locale_save_alphabets_to_C_file() - saves alphabet and identifier alphabet
5584  * to C source file as variables, for later use
5585  * when generating the locale shared library.
5586  *
5587  * return: error code
5588  * fp(in): file pointer where to write the data
5589  * ld(in): locale data
5590  */
5591 static int
5592 locale_save_alphabets_to_C_file (FILE * fp, LOCALE_DATA * ld)
5593 {
5594  assert (ld != NULL);
5595  assert (fp != NULL);
5596 
5597  /* alphabet data */
5598  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "alphabet_a_type", ld->alphabet.a_type, "%d", ld->locale_name);
5599 
5600  if (!(ld->alphabet.do_not_save))
5601  {
5602  const char *alpha_suffix;
5603 
5604  if (ld->alphabet.a_type == ALPHABET_UNICODE)
5605  {
5606  alpha_suffix = "unicode";
5607  }
5608  else if (ld->alphabet.a_type == ALPHABET_ASCII)
5609  {
5610  alpha_suffix = "ascii";
5611  }
5612  else
5613  {
5614  alpha_suffix = (const char *) (ld->locale_name);
5615  }
5616 
5617  (void) locale_save_one_alphabet_to_C_file (fp, &(ld->alphabet), false, alpha_suffix);
5618  }
5619 
5620  /* identifier alphabet data */
5621  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "ident_alphabet_a_type", ld->identif_alphabet.a_type, "%d", ld->locale_name);
5622 
5623  if (!(ld->identif_alphabet.do_not_save))
5624  {
5625  const char *alpha_suffix;
5626  bool save_w_identif = false;
5627 
5628  if (ld->identif_alphabet.a_type == ALPHABET_UNICODE)
5629  {
5630  alpha_suffix = "unicode";
5631  }
5632  else if (ld->identif_alphabet.a_type == ALPHABET_ASCII)
5633  {
5634  alpha_suffix = "ascii";
5635  }
5636  else
5637  {
5638  alpha_suffix = (const char *) (ld->locale_name);
5639  save_w_identif = true;
5640  }
5641 
5642  (void) locale_save_one_alphabet_to_C_file (fp, &(ld->identif_alphabet), save_w_identif, alpha_suffix);
5643  }
5644 
5645  return 0;
5646 }

5648 /*
5649  * locale_save_collation_data_to_C_file() - saves collation data to C source
5650  * file as variables, for later use when generating
5651  * the locale shared library.
5652  *
5653  * return: error code
5654  * fp(in): file pointer where to write the data
5655  * cd(in): collation data
5656  */
5657 static int
5658 locale_save_collation_data_to_C_file (FILE * fp, LOCALE_COLLATION * lc)
5659 {
5660  int i;
5661  COLL_DATA *cd = NULL;
5662 
5663  assert (lc != NULL);
5664  assert (fp != NULL);
5665 
5666  cd = &(lc->opt_coll);
5667 
5668  /* collation constants */
5669  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "coll_id", cd->coll_id, "%d", cd->coll_name);
5670  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_name", cd->coll_name, cd->coll_name);
5671 
5672  /* OPT_COLL.UCA_OPT members */
5673  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "coll_sett_strength", cd->uca_opt.sett_strength, "%d", cd->coll_name);
5674  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "coll_sett_backwards", cd->uca_opt.sett_backwards ? 1 : 0, "%d", cd->coll_name);
5675  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "coll_sett_caseLevel", cd->uca_opt.sett_caseLevel ? 1 : 0, "%d", cd->coll_name);
5676  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "coll_sett_caseFirst", cd->uca_opt.sett_caseFirst, "%d", cd->coll_name);
5677  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "coll_sett_expansions", cd->uca_opt.sett_expansions ? 1 : 0, "%d", cd->coll_name);
5678  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "coll_sett_contr_policy", cd->uca_opt.sett_contr_policy, "%d", cd->coll_name);
5679  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "coll_match_contr", cd->uca_opt.sett_match_contr, "%d", cd->coll_name);
5680 
5681  /* other OPT_COLL members */
5682  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "coll_w_count", cd->w_count, "%d", cd->coll_name);
5683  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "coll_uca_exp_num", cd->uca_exp_num, "%d", cd->coll_name);
5684  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "coll_count_contr", cd->count_contr, "%d", cd->coll_name);
5685 
5686  /* OPT_COLL pointer and array members */
5687  if (cd->w_count > 0)
5688  {
5689  if (!(cd->uca_opt.sett_expansions))
5690  {
5691  if (*(lc->coll_ref.coll_weights_ref) == '\0')
5692  {
5693  sprintf (lc->coll_ref.coll_weights_ref, "coll_weights_%s", cd->coll_name);
5694  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_weights", "unsigned int", "%u", cd->w_count, cd->weights,
5695  cd->coll_name);
5696  }
5697  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_weights_ref", lc->coll_ref.coll_weights_ref, cd->coll_name);
5698  }
5699  else
5700  {
5701  assert (cd->uca_exp_num > 1);
5702 
5703  if (*(lc->coll_ref.coll_uca_w_l13_ref) == '\0')
5704  {
5705  sprintf (lc->coll_ref.coll_uca_w_l13_ref, "coll_uca_w_l13_%s", cd->coll_name);
5706  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_uca_w_l13", "unsigned int", "%u", cd->uca_exp_num * cd->w_count,
5707  cd->uca_w_l13, cd->coll_name);
5708  }
5709  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_uca_w_l13_ref", lc->coll_ref.coll_uca_w_l13_ref, cd->coll_name);
5710 
5711  if (cd->uca_opt.sett_strength >= TAILOR_QUATERNARY)
5712  {
5713  if (*(lc->coll_ref.coll_uca_w_l4_ref) == '\0')
5714  {
5715  sprintf (lc->coll_ref.coll_uca_w_l4_ref, "coll_uca_w_l4_%s", cd->coll_name);
5716  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_uca_w_l4", "unsigned short", "%u", cd->uca_exp_num * cd->w_count,
5717  cd->uca_w_l4, cd->coll_name);
5718  }
5719  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_uca_w_l4_ref", lc->coll_ref.coll_uca_w_l4_ref, cd->coll_name);
5720  }
5721 
5722  if (*(lc->coll_ref.coll_uca_num_ref) == '\0')
5723  {
5724  sprintf (lc->coll_ref.coll_uca_num_ref, "coll_uca_num_%s", cd->coll_name);
5725  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_uca_num", "char", "%d", cd->w_count, cd->uca_num, cd->coll_name);
5726  }
5727  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_uca_num_ref", lc->coll_ref.coll_uca_num_ref, cd->coll_name);
5728  }
5729 
5730  if (*(lc->coll_ref.coll_next_cp_ref) == '\0')
5731  {
5732  sprintf (lc->coll_ref.coll_next_cp_ref, "coll_next_cp_%s", cd->coll_name);
5733  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_next_cp", "unsigned int", "%u", cd->w_count, cd->next_cp, cd->coll_name);
5734  }
5735  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_next_cp_ref", lc->coll_ref.coll_next_cp_ref, cd->coll_name);
5736  }
5737 
5738  if (cd->count_contr > 0)
5739  {
5740  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "coll_contr_min_size", cd->contr_min_size, "%d", cd->coll_name);
5741  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "unsigned int", "coll_cp_first_contr_offset", cd->cp_first_contr_offset, "%u",
5742  cd->coll_name);
5743  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "unsigned int", "coll_cp_first_contr_count", cd->cp_first_contr_count, "%u",
5744  cd->coll_name);
5745 
5746  if (*(lc->coll_ref.coll_contr_list_ref) == '\0')
5747  {
5748  sprintf (lc->coll_ref.coll_contr_list_ref, "coll_contr_list_%s", cd->coll_name);
5749  fprintf (fp, "" DLL_EXPORT_PREFIX "const COLL_CONTRACTION coll_contr_list_%s[] = {", cd->coll_name);
5750  for (i = 0; i < cd->count_contr; i++)
5751  {
5752  fprintf (fp, "\n");
5753  save_contraction_to_C_file (fp, &(cd->contr_list[i]), cd->uca_opt.sett_expansions,
5754  (cd->uca_opt.sett_strength >= TAILOR_QUATERNARY));
5755  if (i < cd->count_contr - 1)
5756  {
5757  fprintf (fp, ", ");
5758  }
5759  }
5760  fprintf (fp, "};\n");
5761  }
5762  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_contr_list_ref", lc->coll_ref.coll_contr_list_ref, cd->coll_name);
5763 
5764  if (*(lc->coll_ref.coll_cp_first_contr_array_ref) == '\0')
5765  {
5766  sprintf (lc->coll_ref.coll_cp_first_contr_array_ref, "coll_cp_first_contr_array_%s", cd->coll_name);
5767  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_cp_first_contr_array", "int", "%d", (int) cd->cp_first_contr_count,
5768  cd->cp_first_contr_array, cd->coll_name);
5769  }
5770  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_cp_first_contr_array_ref", lc->coll_ref.coll_cp_first_contr_array_ref,
5771  cd->coll_name);
5772 
5773  }
5774 
5775  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "coll_checksum", cd->checksum, cd->coll_name);
5776  return 0;
5777 }

5779 /*
5780  * locale_save_console_conv_to_C_file() - saves console conversion data to
5781  * binary file
5782  *
5783  * return: zero if save is successful, non-zero otherwise
5784  * fp(in): file descriptor
5785  * tc(in): console conversion info
5786  */
5787 static int
5788 locale_save_console_conv_to_C_file (FILE * fp, LOCALE_DATA * ld)
5789 {
5790  int i;
5791 
5792  TEXT_CONVERSION *tc;
5793 
5794  assert (ld != NULL);
5795  assert (fp != NULL);
5796 
5797  tc = &(ld->txt_conv);
5798 
5799  /* TEXT_CONVERSION non-array members */
5800  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "tc_conv_type", tc->conv_type, "%d", ld->locale_name);
5801 
5802  if (tc->conv_type != TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE && tc->conv_type != TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_2BYTE)
5803  {
5804  return 0;
5805  }
5806 
5807  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "tc_is_lead_byte", "unsigned char", "%u", 256, tc->byte_flag, ld->locale_name);
5808  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "unsigned int", "tc_utf8_first_cp", tc->utf8_first_cp, "%u", ld->locale_name);
5809  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "unsigned int", "tc_utf8_last_cp", tc->utf8_last_cp, "%u", ld->locale_name);
5810  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "unsigned int", "tc_text_first_cp", tc->text_first_cp, "%u", ld->locale_name);
5811  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "unsigned int", "tc_text_last_cp", tc->text_last_cp, "%u", ld->locale_name);
5812 
5813  assert (tc->win_codepages != NULL);
5814  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "tc_win_codepages", tc->win_codepages, ld->locale_name);
5815 
5816  assert (tc->nl_lang_str != NULL);
5817  PRINT_STRING_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "tc_nl_lang_str", tc->nl_lang_str, ld->locale_name);
5818 
5819  assert (tc->utf8_last_cp > tc->utf8_first_cp);
5820  assert (tc->utf8_to_text != NULL);
5821 
5822  fprintf (fp, "" DLL_EXPORT_PREFIX "const CONV_CP_TO_BYTES tc_utf8_to_text_%s[] = { \n", ld->locale_name);
5823  for (i = 0; i < (int) (tc->utf8_last_cp - tc->utf8_first_cp + 1); i++)
5824  {
5825  fprintf (fp, "{ %u, ", tc->utf8_to_text[i].size);
5826  PRINT_STRING_TO_C_FILE (fp, tc->utf8_to_text[i].bytes, tc->utf8_to_text[i].size);
5827  fprintf (fp, "},\n");
5828  }
5829  fprintf (fp, "};\n");
5830 
5831  assert (tc->text_last_cp > tc->text_first_cp);
5832  assert (tc->text_to_utf8 != NULL);
5833 
5834  fprintf (fp, "" DLL_EXPORT_PREFIX "const CONV_CP_TO_BYTES tc_text_to_utf8_%s[] = { \n", ld->locale_name);
5835  for (i = 0; i < (int) (tc->text_last_cp - tc->text_first_cp + 1); i++)
5836  {
5837  fprintf (fp, "{ %u, ", tc->text_to_utf8[i].size);
5838  PRINT_STRING_TO_C_FILE (fp, tc->text_to_utf8[i].bytes, tc->text_to_utf8[i].size);
5839  fprintf (fp, "},\n");
5840  }
5841  fprintf (fp, "};\n");
5842 
5843  return 0;
5844 }
5845 
5846 /*
5847  * str_pop_token() - Extracts a token from a string;
5848  * A token is a sub-string surrounded by whitespaces.
5849  * return: string token
5850  * str_p(in): buffer with tokens
5851  * token_p(in/out): returned token string
5852  * next_p(in/out): pointer to next token or NULL if no more tokens
5853  *
5854  * Note : When found the token characters are copied into a new string
5855  * and returned.
5856  * The pointer to the first character following the new token in
5857  * the buffer is returned.
5858  */
5859 static int
5860 str_pop_token (char *str_p, char **token_p, char **next_p)
5861 {
5862  char *p, *end, *token = NULL;
5863  int length;
5864 
5865  assert (str_p != NULL);
5866  assert (token_p != NULL);
5867  assert (next_p != NULL);
5868 
5869  p = str_p;
5870  while (char_isspace ((int) *p) && *p != '\0')
5871  {
5872  p++;
5873  }
5874  end = p;
5875  while (!char_isspace ((int) *end) && *end != '\0')
5876  {
5877  end++;
5878  }
5879 
5880  length = (int) (end - p);
5881  if (length > 0)
5882  {
5883  token = (char *) malloc (length + 1);
5884  if (token == NULL)
5885  {
5886  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", ER_LOC_INIT, true);
5887  return ER_LOC_INIT;
5888  }
5889  assert (token != NULL);
5890 
5891  strncpy (token, p, length);
5892  token[length] = '\0';
5893  }
5894  else
5895  {
5896  /* no more tokens */
5897  end = NULL;
5898  }
5899 
5900  *token_p = token;
5901  *next_p = end;
5902  return NO_ERROR;
5903 }
5904 
5905 /*
5906  * dump_locale_alphabet - dump the selected ALPHABET_DATA structure
5907  * in human-readable text format.
5908  * Returns : NO_ERROR.
5909  * ad(in) : the ALPHABET_DATA to be dumped in text format.
5910  * dl_settings(in): the commmand line options encoded intoa binary masked int.
5911  * lower_bound(in): the starting codepoint for the range of items which
5912  * -w or -c will dump.
5913  * upper_bound(in) : the ending codepoint for the range of items which
5914  * -w or -c will dump.
5915  */
5916 static int
5917 dump_locale_alphabet (ALPHABET_DATA * ad, int dl_settings, int lower_bound, int upper_bound)
5918 {
5919 #define DUMP_CP_BUF_SIZE 128
5920  int i, cp;
5921  unsigned char utf8_buf[INTL_UTF8_MAX_CHAR_SIZE + 1];
5922  unsigned int *case_buf;
5923  char out_case[DUMP_CP_BUF_SIZE];
5924  char out_cp[DUMP_CP_BUF_SIZE];
5925 
5926  assert (ad != NULL);
5927  assert (lower_bound <= upper_bound);
5928 
5929  printf ("Alphabet type: ");
5930  if (ad->a_type == ALPHABET_UNICODE)
5931  {
5932  printf ("Unicode\n");
5933  }
5934  else if (ad->a_type == ALPHABET_ASCII)
5935  {
5936  printf ("ASCII\n");
5937  }
5938  else
5939  {
5940  assert (ad->a_type == ALPHABET_TAILORED);
5941  printf ("Tailored\n");
5942  }
5943 
5944  printf ("Letter count: %d\n", ad->l_count);
5945  if (ad->l_count > 0)
5946  {
5947  printf ("Lower multiplier: %d\n", ad->lower_multiplier);
5948  printf ("Upper multiplier: %d\n", ad->upper_multiplier);
5949  }
5950 
5951  for (cp = lower_bound; cp < upper_bound; cp++)
5952  {
5953  memset (utf8_buf, 0, INTL_UTF8_MAX_CHAR_SIZE + 1);
5954  intl_cp_to_utf8 (cp, utf8_buf);
5955  printf ("CP: Ux%04X | %-4s", cp, (cp > 0x0020 ? utf8_buf : (unsigned char *) ""));
5956  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_ALPHABET_LOWER) != 0)
5957  {
5958  bool print_case = true;
5959  memset (out_cp, 0, sizeof (out_cp));
5960  memset (out_case, 0, sizeof (out_case));
5961 
5962  case_buf = &(ad->lower_cp[cp * ad->lower_multiplier]);
5963 
5964  for (i = 0; i < ad->lower_multiplier; i++)
5965  {
5966  char temp_cp[8];
5967 
5968  if (case_buf[i] == 0)
5969  {
5970  break;
5971  }
5972 
5973  if (case_buf[i] < 0x20)
5974  {
5975  print_case = false;
5976  }
5977  memset (utf8_buf, 0, sizeof (utf8_buf));
5978  intl_cp_to_utf8 (case_buf[i], utf8_buf);
5979  strcat (out_case, (char *) utf8_buf);
5980  snprintf (temp_cp, sizeof (temp_cp) - 1, "Ux%04X", case_buf[i]);
5981  strcat (out_cp, temp_cp);
5982  }
5983  printf (" | Lower : CP(s): %-12s, lower char(s): %-12s", out_cp, (print_case ? out_case : ""));
5984  }
5985  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_ALPHABET_UPPER) != 0)
5986  {
5987  bool print_case = true;
5988  memset (out_cp, 0, sizeof (out_cp));
5989  memset (out_case, 0, sizeof (out_case));
5990 
5991  case_buf = &(ad->upper_cp[cp * ad->upper_multiplier]);
5992 
5993  for (i = 0; i < ad->upper_multiplier; i++)
5994  {
5995  char temp_cp[8];
5996 
5997  if (case_buf[i] == 0)
5998  {
5999  break;
6000  }
6001 
6002  if (case_buf[i] < 0x20)
6003  {
6004  print_case = false;
6005  }
6006 
6007  memset (utf8_buf, 0, sizeof (utf8_buf));
6008  intl_cp_to_utf8 (case_buf[i], utf8_buf);
6009  strcat (out_case, (char *) utf8_buf);
6010  snprintf (temp_cp, sizeof (temp_cp) - 1, "Ux%04X", case_buf[i]);
6011  strcat (out_cp, temp_cp);
6012  }
6013  printf (" | Upper : CP(s): %-12s, upper char(s): %-12s", out_cp, (print_case ? out_case : ""));
6014  }
6015  printf ("\n");
6016  }
6017  return NO_ERROR;
6018 }
6019 
6020 /*
6021  * dump_locale_collation - dump the selected COLL_DATA structure
6022  * in human-readable text format.
6023  * Returns : NO_ERROR.
6024  * coll(in) : the COLL_DATA to be dumped in text format.
6025  * dl_settings(in): the commmand line options encoded intoa binary masked int.
6026  * lower_bound(in): the starting codepoint for the range of items which
6027  * -w or -c will dump.
6028  * upper_bound(in) : the ending codepoint for the range of items which
6029  * -w or -c will dump.
6030  */
6031 static int
6032 dump_locale_collation (COLL_DATA * coll, int dl_settings, int start_value, int end_value)
6033 {
6034  unsigned int *coll_key_list = NULL;
6035  int coll_key_list_cnt = 0;
6036  int lower_bound = 0;
6037  int upper_bound = 0;
6038  int err_status = NO_ERROR;
6039  int cp, i;
6040 
6041  assert (coll != NULL);
6042 
6043  lower_bound = 0;
6044  upper_bound = coll->w_count;
6045  if (start_value > lower_bound)
6046  {
6047  lower_bound = start_value;
6048  }
6049  if (end_value > 0 && end_value < upper_bound)
6050  {
6051  /* if an upper bound is specified, use the "+1" to make sure that the upper bound codepoint is included in the
6052  * dump file. */
6053  upper_bound = end_value + 1;
6054  }
6055 
6056  printf ("\n");
6057  printf ("* Collation: %s | id: %d | checksum: %s *\n", coll->coll_name, coll->coll_id, coll->checksum);
6058  printf ("Max codepoints: %d\n", coll->w_count);
6059  printf ("Level: %d\n", coll->uca_opt.sett_strength);
6060  printf ("Expansions: %s\n", coll->uca_opt.sett_expansions ? "yes" : "no");
6061  if (coll->uca_opt.sett_expansions)
6062  {
6063  printf ("Expansion CE num: %d\n", coll->uca_exp_num);
6064  }
6065  printf ("Contractions: %d\n", coll->count_contr);
6066  if (coll->count_contr > 0)
6067  {
6068  printf ("Contraction min size: %d\n", coll->contr_min_size);
6069  }
6070 
6071  assert (coll->w_count > 0);
6072 
6073  if (upper_bound < lower_bound)
6074  {
6075  err_status = ER_LOC_GEN;
6076  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (msgcat_message
6077  (MSGCAT_CATALOG_UTILS, MSGCAT_UTIL_SET_DUMPLOCALE, DUMPLOCALE_MSG_INVALID_CP_RANGE), ER_LOC_GEN,
6078  true);
6079  goto exit;
6080  }
6081 
6082  /* Dump collation information, cp and next_cp info, ordered by cp. */
6083  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_COLLATION_CP_ORDER) != 0)
6084  {
6085  printf ("\n");
6086  printf ("* Codepoint collation info (codepoint order) *\n");
6087  for (cp = lower_bound; cp < upper_bound; cp++)
6088  {
6089  unsigned int next_id;
6090 
6091  assert (cp >= 0 && cp < coll->w_count);
6092 
6093  dump_collation_codepoint (coll, cp, true, true);
6094 
6095  next_id = coll->next_cp[cp];
6096  printf (" | Next : ");
6097 
6098  dump_collation_key (coll, next_id, true, true);
6099 
6100  printf ("\n");
6101  }
6102  }
6103 
6104  if (coll->count_contr > 0 && (dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_COLLATION_CP_ORDER) != 0)
6105  {
6106  printf ("\n");
6107  printf ("* Contraction collation info (contraction order) *\n");
6108  for (i = 0; i < coll->count_contr; i++)
6109  {
6110  COLL_CONTRACTION *contr = &(coll->contr_list[i]);
6111 
6112  dump_collation_contr (coll, contr, true, true);
6113  printf (" | Next :");
6114 
6115  dump_collation_key (coll, contr->next, true, true);
6116 
6117  printf ("\n");
6118  }
6119  }
6120 
6121  /* Dump weight list and corresponding codepoints, ordered by weight. */
6122  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_COLLATION_WEIGHT_ORDER) != 0)
6123  {
6124  int keys_same_weight = 1;
6125  int cp_count = upper_bound - lower_bound;
6126  bool use_expansions;
6127 
6128  printf ("\n");
6129  printf ("* Collation info (weight order) *\n");
6130  coll_key_list_cnt = cp_count + coll->count_contr;
6131  coll_key_list = (unsigned int *) malloc (coll_key_list_cnt * sizeof (unsigned int));
6132  if (coll_key_list == NULL)
6133  {
6134  err_status = ER_LOC_INIT;
6135  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", ER_LOC_INIT, true);
6136  goto exit;
6137  }
6138 
6139  for (cp = lower_bound; cp < upper_bound; cp++)
6140  {
6141  coll_key_list[cp - lower_bound] = cp;
6142  }
6143 
6144  for (i = 0; i < coll->count_contr; i++)
6145  {
6146  coll_key_list[i + cp_count] = i | INTL_MASK_CONTR;
6147  }
6148 
6149  /* Order by weight. */
6150  use_expansions = coll->uca_opt.sett_expansions;
6151 
6152  dump_coll_data = coll;
6153  if (use_expansions)
6154  {
6155  qsort (coll_key_list, coll_key_list_cnt, sizeof (unsigned int), comp_func_coll_uca_exp_fo);
6156  }
6157  else
6158  {
6159  qsort (coll_key_list, coll_key_list_cnt, sizeof (unsigned int), comp_func_coll_uca_simple_weights_fo);
6160  }
6161 
6162  /* Dump ordered (weight, key id) tuples. */
6163  for (i = 0; i < coll_key_list_cnt; i++)
6164  {
6165  bool same_weights = false;
6166 
6167  if (i > 0)
6168  {
6169  if (use_expansions)
6170  {
6171  same_weights =
6172  (comp_func_coll_uca_exp (&(coll_key_list[i]), &(coll_key_list[i - 1])) == 0) ? true : false;
6173  }
6174  else
6175  {
6176  same_weights =
6177  (comp_func_coll_uca_simple_weights (&(coll_key_list[i]), &(coll_key_list[i - 1])) ==
6178  0) ? true : false;
6179  }
6180  }
6181 
6182  if (i > 0 && !same_weights)
6183  {
6184  if (keys_same_weight > 1)
6185  {
6186  printf (" Keys same weight : %d\n", keys_same_weight);
6187  }
6188  else
6189  {
6190  printf ("\n");
6191  }
6192 
6193  dump_collation_key (coll, coll_key_list[i], true, false);
6194  keys_same_weight = 1;
6195  }
6196  else
6197  {
6198  printf ("\n");
6199  dump_collation_key (coll, coll_key_list[i], true, false);
6200  keys_same_weight++;
6201  }
6202 
6203  printf (" | ");
6204 
6205  dump_collation_key (coll, coll_key_list[i], false, true);
6206  }
6207  }
6208 exit:
6209  if (coll_key_list != NULL)
6210  {
6211  free (coll_key_list);
6212  }
6213 
6214  return err_status;
6215 }

6217 /*
6218  * locale_dump - output the selected information on locale data in
6219  * human-readable text format.
6220  * Returns : error status.
6221  * data(in): the locale data to be dumped in text format.
6222  * lf(in) : the LOCALE_FILE i.e. binary file from which ld was imported.
6223  * dl_settings(in): the commmand line options encoded intoa binary masked int.
6224  * start_value(in): the starting codepoint for the range of items which
6225  * -w or -c will dump.
6226  * end_value(in) : the ending codepoint for the range of items which
6227  * -w or -c will dump.
6228  */
6229 int
6230 locale_dump (void *data, LOCALE_FILE * lf, int dl_settings, int start_value, int end_value)
6231 {
6232  int i;
6233  int lower_bound = 0;
6234  int upper_bound = 0;
6235  int alphabet_settings;
6236  int err_status = NO_ERROR;
6237  LANG_LOCALE_DATA *lld = NULL;
6238 
6239  assert (data != NULL);
6240  assert (lf != NULL);
6241  assert (start_value <= end_value);
6242 
6243  lld = (LANG_LOCALE_DATA *) data;
6244 
6245  printf ("*************************************************\n");
6246  printf ("Locale data for: %s\nLibrary file: %s\n", lf->locale_name, lf->lib_file);
6247  printf ("Locale string: %s\n", lld->lang_name);
6248  printf ("Locale checksum: %s\n", lld->checksum);
6249 
6250  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_CALENDAR) != 0)
6251  {
6252  printf ("\n * Calendar *\n");
6253  printf ("Date format: %s\n", lld->date_format);
6254  printf ("Time format: %s\n", lld->time_format);
6255  printf ("Datetime format: %s\n", lld->datetime_format);
6256  printf ("Timestamp format: %s\n", lld->timestamp_format);
6257  printf ("Datetime_tz format: %s\n", lld->datetimetz_format);
6258  printf ("Timestamp_tz format: %s\n", lld->timestamptz_format);
6259 
6260  printf ("\nAbbreviated month names:\n");
6261  for (i = 0; i < CAL_MONTH_COUNT; i++)
6262  {
6263  printf ("%d. %s\n", (i + 1), lld->month_short_name[i]);
6264  }
6265  printf ("\nAbbreviated month names, sorted for tokenizer:\n");
6266  for (i = 0; i < CAL_MONTH_COUNT; i++)
6267  {
6268  printf ("%d. %s = month %d\n", (i + 1), lld->month_short_name[(int) (lld->month_short_parse_order[i])],
6269  (int) (lld->month_short_parse_order[i]) + 1);
6270  }
6271 
6272  printf ("\nWide month names:\n");
6273  for (i = 0; i < CAL_MONTH_COUNT; i++)
6274  {
6275  printf ("%d. %s\n", (i + 1), lld->month_name[i]);
6276  }
6277  printf ("\nWide month names, sorted for tokenizer:\n");
6278  for (i = 0; i < CAL_MONTH_COUNT; i++)
6279  {
6280  printf ("%d. %s = month %d\n", (i + 1), lld->month_name[(int) (lld->month_parse_order[i])],
6281  (int) (lld->month_parse_order[i]) + 1);
6282  }
6283 
6284  printf ("\nAbbreviated weekday names:\n");
6285  for (i = 0; i < CAL_DAY_COUNT; i++)
6286  {
6287  printf ("%d. %s\n", (i + 1), lld->day_short_name[i]);
6288  }
6289  printf ("\nAbbreviated weekday names, sorted for parse order:\n");
6290  for (i = 0; i < CAL_DAY_COUNT; i++)
6291  {
6292  printf ("%d. %s = weekday %d\n", (i + 1), lld->day_short_name[(int) (lld->day_short_parse_order[i])],
6293  (int) (lld->day_short_parse_order[i]) + 1);
6294  }
6295 
6296  printf ("\nWide weekday names:\n");
6297  for (i = 0; i < CAL_DAY_COUNT; i++)
6298  {
6299  printf ("%d. %s\n", (i + 1), lld->day_name[i]);
6300  }
6301  printf ("\nWide weekday names, sorted for tokenizer:\n");
6302  for (i = 0; i < CAL_DAY_COUNT; i++)
6303  {
6304  printf ("%d. %s = weekday %d\n", (i + 1), lld->day_name[(int) (lld->day_parse_order[i])],
6305  (int) (lld->day_parse_order[i]) + 1);
6306  }
6307 
6308  printf ("\nDay periods:\n");
6309  for (i = 0; i < CAL_AM_PM_COUNT; i++)
6310  {
6311  printf ("%d. %s\n", (i + 1), lld->am_pm[i]);
6312  }
6313  printf ("\nDay periods, sorted for tokenizer:\n");
6314  for (i = 0; i < CAL_AM_PM_COUNT; i++)
6315  {
6316  printf ("%d. %s = day period %d\n", (i + 1), lld->am_pm[(int) (lld->am_pm_parse_order[i])],
6317  (int) (lld->am_pm_parse_order[i]) + 1);
6318  }
6319  }
6320 
6321  /* Display numbering information. */
6322  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_NUMBERING) != 0)
6323  {
6324  printf ("\n * Numbers *\n");
6325  printf ("Decimal separator: <%c>\n", lld->number_decimal_sym);
6326  printf ("Separator for digit grouping: <%c>\n", lld->number_group_sym);
6327  printf ("Default currency ISO code: %s\n", intl_get_money_ISO_symbol (lld->default_currency_code));
6328  }
6329 
6330  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_ALPHABET) != 0)
6331  {
6332  lower_bound = 0;
6333  upper_bound = lld->alphabet.l_count;
6334  if (start_value > lower_bound)
6335  {
6336  lower_bound = start_value;
6337  }
6338  if (end_value > 0 && end_value < upper_bound)
6339  {
6340  /* if an upper bound is specified, use the "+1" to make sure that the upper bound codepoint is included in
6341  * the dump file. */
6342  upper_bound = end_value + 1;
6343  }
6344  }
6345 
6346  if (upper_bound < lower_bound)
6347  {
6348  err_status = ER_LOC_GEN;
6349  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (msgcat_message
6350  (MSGCAT_CATALOG_UTILS, MSGCAT_UTIL_SET_DUMPLOCALE, DUMPLOCALE_MSG_INVALID_CP_RANGE), ER_LOC_GEN,
6351  true);
6352  goto exit;
6353  }
6354 
6355  /* Dump alphabet data. */
6356  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_ALPHABET) != 0)
6357  {
6358  alphabet_settings = 0;
6359  alphabet_settings |= (dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_ALPHABET_LOWER);
6360  alphabet_settings |= (dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_ALPHABET_UPPER);
6361  printf ("\n * Alphabet data *\n");
6362  dump_locale_alphabet (&(lld->alphabet), alphabet_settings, lower_bound, upper_bound);
6363  }
6364 
6365  /* Dump identifier alphabet data. */
6366  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_IDENTIFIER_ALPHABET) != 0)
6367  {
6368  alphabet_settings = 0;
6369  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_IDENTIFIER_ALPHABET_LOWER) != 0)
6370  {
6371  alphabet_settings |= DUMPLOCALE_IS_ALPHABET_LOWER;
6372  }
6373  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_IDENTIFIER_ALPHABET_UPPER) != 0)
6374  {
6375  alphabet_settings |= DUMPLOCALE_IS_ALPHABET_UPPER;
6376  }
6377 
6378  printf ("\n");
6379  printf ("* Identifier alphabet data *\n");
6380  dump_locale_alphabet (&(lld->ident_alphabet), alphabet_settings, lower_bound, upper_bound);
6381  }
6382 
6383  /* Dump normalization data. */
6384  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_NORMALIZATION) != 0)
6385  {
6386  printf ("\n");
6387  printf ("* Normalization data *\n");
6388  dump_locale_normalization (&(lld->unicode_norm));
6389  }
6390 
6391  /* Dump normalization data. */
6392  if ((dl_settings & DUMPLOCALE_IS_TEXT_CONV) != 0)
6393  {
6394  printf ("\n");
6395  printf ("* Console conversion data *\n");
6396  dump_console_conversion (lld->txt_conv);
6397  }
6398 
6399 exit:
6400  return err_status;
6401 }
6402 
6403 /*
6404  * locale_dump_lib_collations() - output the selected information on
6405  * collations data in human-readable text
6406  * format.
6407  * return: error code
6408  * lib_handle(in):
6409  * lf(in): locale file info
6410  * dl_settings(in):
6411  * lower_bound(in):
6412  * upper_bound(in):
6413  */
6414 int
6415 locale_dump_lib_collations (void *lib_handle, const LOCALE_FILE * lf, int dl_settings, int start_value, int end_value)
6416 {
6417  int err_status = NO_ERROR;
6418  int i, count_coll_to_load;
6419  COLL_DATA coll;
6420 
6421  assert (lib_handle != NULL);
6422  assert (lf != NULL);
6423  assert (lf->locale_name != NULL);
6424 
6425  /* collation data */
6426  err_status = lang_load_count_coll_from_lib (&count_coll_to_load, lib_handle, lf);
6427  if (err_status != NO_ERROR)
6428  {
6429  goto exit;
6430  }
6431 
6432  printf ("\n\n* Collations: %d collations found *\n", count_coll_to_load);
6433 
6434  for (i = 0; i < count_coll_to_load; i++)
6435  {
6436  /* get name of collation */
6437  char *coll_name = NULL;
6438 
6439  memset (&coll, 0, sizeof (COLL_DATA));
6440 
6441  err_status = lang_load_get_coll_name_from_lib (i, &coll_name, lib_handle, lf);
6442  if (err_status != NO_ERROR)
6443  {
6444  goto exit;
6445  }
6446 
6447  assert (strlen (coll_name) < (int) sizeof (coll.coll_name));
6448  strncpy (coll.coll_name, coll_name, sizeof (coll.coll_name) - 1);
6449 
6450  err_status = lang_load_coll_from_lib (&coll, lib_handle, lf);
6451  if (err_status != NO_ERROR)
6452  {
6453  goto exit;
6454  }
6455 
6456  err_status = dump_locale_collation (&coll, dl_settings, start_value, end_value);
6457  if (err_status != NO_ERROR)
6458  {
6459  goto exit;
6460  }
6461  printf ("\n\n\n");
6462  }
6463 
6464 exit:
6465  return err_status;
6466 }
6467 
6468 /*
6469  * comp_func_coll_uca_simple_weights_fo - compare function for sorting
6470  * collatable elements according to simple weights order
6471  * but applies full order
6472  *
6473  * Note: This function uses 'comp_func_coll_uca_simple_weights' but applies
6474  * a full order.
6475  * The purpose is to provide a 'deterministic comparison' to eliminate
6476  * unpredictable results of sort algorithm (qsort).
6477  */
6478 static int
6479 comp_func_coll_uca_simple_weights_fo (const void *arg1, const void *arg2)
6480 {
6481  unsigned int pos1;
6482  unsigned int pos2;
6483  int cmp;
6484 
6485  pos1 = *((unsigned int *) arg1);
6486  pos2 = *((unsigned int *) arg2);
6487 
6488  cmp = comp_func_coll_uca_simple_weights (arg1, arg2);
6489 
6490  return (cmp == 0) ? (int) (pos1 - pos2) : cmp;
6491 }
6492 
6493 /*
6494  * comp_func_coll_uca_simple_weights - compare function for sorting collatable
6495  * elements according to simple weights order
6496  *
6497  * Note: this function is used by dump_locale tool
6498  * The elements in array are 32 bit unsigned integers, keys which
6499  * may be Unicode points or contractions (when highest bit is set)
6500  *
6501  */
6502 static int
6503 comp_func_coll_uca_simple_weights (const void *arg1, const void *arg2)
6504 {
6505  unsigned int pos1;
6506  unsigned int pos2;
6507  unsigned int wv1, wv2;
6508  COLL_DATA *coll = dump_coll_data;
6509 
6510  pos1 = *((unsigned int *) arg1);
6511  pos2 = *((unsigned int *) arg2);
6512 
6513  assert (coll != NULL);
6514 
6515  if (INTL_IS_NEXT_CONTR (pos1))
6516  {
6517  wv1 = coll->contr_list[INTL_GET_NEXT_CONTR_ID (pos1)].wv;
6518  }
6519  else
6520  {
6521  wv1 = coll->weights[pos1];
6522  }
6523 
6524  if (INTL_IS_NEXT_CONTR (pos2))
6525  {
6526  wv2 = coll->contr_list[INTL_GET_NEXT_CONTR_ID (pos2)].wv;
6527  }
6528  else
6529  {
6530  wv2 = coll->weights[pos2];
6531  }
6532 
6533  return wv1 - wv2;
6534 }
6535 
6536 /*
6537  * comp_func_coll_uca_exp_fo - compare function for sorting collatable
6538  * elements according to UCA algorithm,
6539  * with full order
6540  *
6541  * Note: This function uses 'comp_func_coll_uca_exp' but applies a full order
6542  * The purpose is to provide a 'deterministic comparison' to eliminate
6543  * unpredictable results of sort algorithm (qsort).
6544  */
6545 static int
6546 comp_func_coll_uca_exp_fo (const void *arg1, const void *arg2)
6547 {
6548  unsigned int pos1;
6549  unsigned int pos2;
6550  int cmp;
6551 
6552  pos1 = *((unsigned int *) arg1);
6553  pos2 = *((unsigned int *) arg2);
6554 
6555  cmp = comp_func_coll_uca_exp (arg1, arg2);
6556 
6557  return (cmp == 0) ? (int) (pos1 - pos2) : cmp;
6558 }
6559 
6560 /*
6561  * comp_func_coll_uca_exp - compare function for sorting collatable elements
6562  * according to UCA algorithm
6563  *
6564  * Note: this function is used by dump_locale tool
6565  * The elements in array are 32 bit unsigned integers, keys which
6566  * may be Unicode points or contractions (when highest bit is set)
6567  *
6568  */
6569 static int
6570 comp_func_coll_uca_exp (const void *arg1, const void *arg2)
6571 {
6572  unsigned int pos1;
6573  unsigned int pos2;
6574  COLL_DATA *coll = dump_coll_data;
6575  unsigned char utf8_buf_1[INTL_UTF8_MAX_CHAR_SIZE + 1];
6576  unsigned char utf8_buf_2[INTL_UTF8_MAX_CHAR_SIZE + 1];
6577  char *str1;
6578  char *str2;
6579  int size1, size2;
6580 
6581  pos1 = *((unsigned int *) arg1);
6582  pos2 = *((unsigned int *) arg2);
6583 
6584  assert (coll != NULL);
6585 
6586  /* build strings from the two keys and use the UCA collation function */
6587  if (INTL_IS_NEXT_CONTR (pos1))
6588  {
6589  str1 = coll->contr_list[INTL_GET_NEXT_CONTR_ID (pos1)].c_buf;
6590  size1 = coll->contr_list[INTL_GET_NEXT_CONTR_ID (pos1)].size;
6591  }
6592  else
6593  {
6594  size1 = intl_cp_to_utf8 (pos1, utf8_buf_1);
6595  utf8_buf_1[size1] = '\0';
6596  str1 = (char *) utf8_buf_1;
6597  }
6598 
6599  if (INTL_IS_NEXT_CONTR (pos2))
6600  {
6601  str2 = coll->contr_list[INTL_GET_NEXT_CONTR_ID (pos2)].c_buf;
6602  size2 = coll->contr_list[INTL_GET_NEXT_CONTR_ID (pos2)].size;
6603  }
6604  else
6605  {
6606  size2 = intl_cp_to_utf8 (pos2, utf8_buf_2);
6607  utf8_buf_2[size2] = '\0';
6608  str2 = (char *) utf8_buf_2;
6609  }
6610 
6611  return lang_strmatch_utf8_uca_w_coll_data (coll, false, (const unsigned char *) str1, size1,
6612  (const unsigned char *) str2, size2, NULL, false, NULL);
6613 }

6615 /*
6616  * dump_collation_key - prints information on collation key
6617  * (codepoint or contraction)
6618  * Returns :
6619  * coll(in) : collation data
6620  * key(in) : key to print
6621  * print_weight(in): true if weight should be printed
6622  * print_contr(in): true if contraction info should be printed
6623  */
6624 static void
6625 dump_collation_key (COLL_DATA * coll, const unsigned int key, bool print_weight, bool print_key)
6626 {
6627  if (INTL_IS_NEXT_CONTR (key))
6628  {
6629  unsigned int contr_id = INTL_GET_NEXT_CONTR_ID (key);
6630  COLL_CONTRACTION *contr = &(coll->contr_list[contr_id]);
6631 
6632  dump_collation_contr (coll, contr, print_weight, print_key);
6633  }
6634  else
6635  {
6636  dump_collation_codepoint (coll, key, print_weight, print_key);
6637  }
6638 }

6640 /*
6641  * dump_collation_contr - prints information on collation contraction
6642  * Returns :
6643  * coll(in) : collation data
6644  * contr(in) : contraction
6645  * print_weight(in): true if weight should be printed
6646  * print_contr(in): true if contraction info should be printed
6647  */
6648 static void
6649 dump_collation_contr (COLL_DATA * coll, const COLL_CONTRACTION * contr, bool print_weight, bool print_contr)
6650 {
6651  int i;
6652 
6653  assert (contr != NULL);
6654 
6655  assert (contr->cp_count <= LOC_MAX_UCA_CHARS_SEQ);
6656 
6657  if (print_contr)
6658  {
6659  unsigned int cp_list[LOC_MAX_UCA_CHARS_SEQ];
6660  bool print_utf8 = true;
6661  int cp_count;
6662 
6663  intl_utf8_to_cp_list ((const unsigned char *) contr->c_buf, strlen (contr->c_buf), cp_list, sizeof (cp_list),
6664  &cp_count);
6665 
6666  assert (cp_count == contr->cp_count);
6667 
6668  printf ("Contr: ");
6669  for (i = 0; i < cp_count; i++)
6670  {
6671  printf ("Ux%04X ", cp_list[i]);
6672  if (cp_list[i] < 0x20)
6673  {
6674  print_utf8 = false;
6675  }
6676  }
6677 
6678  if (print_utf8)
6679  {
6680  printf (" | %s", contr->c_buf);
6681  }
6682  }
6683 
6684  if (!print_weight)
6685  {
6686  return;
6687  }
6688 
6689  if (coll->uca_exp_num <= 1)
6690  {
6691  printf (" | Weight : %04x", contr->wv);
6692  return;
6693  }
6694 
6695  assert (contr->uca_num > 0 && contr->uca_num <= MAX_UCA_EXP_CE);
6696 
6697  printf (" | Weight : ");
6698  for (i = 0; i < (int) contr->uca_num; i++)
6699  {
6700  printf ("[%04X.", UCA_GET_L1_W (contr->uca_w_l13[i]));
6701  printf ("%04X.", UCA_GET_L2_W (contr->uca_w_l13[i]));
6702  printf ("%04X.", UCA_GET_L3_W (contr->uca_w_l13[i]));
6703  if (coll->uca_opt.sett_strength >= TAILOR_QUATERNARY)
6704  {
6705  printf ("%04X]", contr->uca_w_l4[i]);
6706  }
6707  else
6708  {
6709  printf ("]");
6710  }
6711  }
6712 }

6714 /*
6715  * dump_collation_codepoint - prints information on collation codepoint
6716  * Returns :
6717  * coll(in) : collation data
6718  * cp(in) : codepoint
6719  * print_weight(in): true if weight should be printed
6720  */
6721 static void
6722 dump_collation_codepoint (COLL_DATA * coll, const unsigned int cp, bool print_weight, bool print_cp)
6723 {
6724  assert (cp <= INTL_MAX_UNICODE_CP_ALLOWED);
6725 
6726  if (print_cp)
6727  {
6728  unsigned char utf8_buf[INTL_UTF8_MAX_CHAR_SIZE + 1];
6729 
6730  memset (utf8_buf, 0, INTL_UTF8_MAX_CHAR_SIZE + 1);
6731 
6732  intl_cp_to_utf8 (cp, utf8_buf);
6733 
6734  printf ("CP: Ux%04X | %-4s", cp, ((cp > 0x20) ? utf8_buf : (unsigned char *) ""));
6735  }
6736 
6737  if (!print_weight)
6738  {
6739  return;
6740  }
6741 
6742  if (coll->uca_exp_num <= 1)
6743  {
6744  printf (" | Weight%s: %04x", ((int) cp < coll->w_count) ? "" : "(Computed)",
6745  (((int) cp < coll->w_count) ? (coll->weights[cp]) : (cp + 1)));
6746  return;
6747  }
6748 
6749  assert (coll->uca_exp_num > 1);
6750  assert (coll->uca_exp_num <= MAX_UCA_EXP_CE);
6751 
6752  if ((int) cp < coll->w_count)
6753  {
6754  int i;
6755  UCA_L13_W *uca_w_l13 = &(coll->uca_w_l13[cp * coll->uca_exp_num]);
6756 
6757  printf (" | Weight : ");
6758 
6759  assert (coll->uca_num[cp] >= 1);
6760  assert (coll->uca_num[cp] <= MAX_UCA_EXP_CE);
6761 
6762  for (i = 0; i < coll->uca_num[cp]; i++)
6763  {
6764  printf ("[%04X.", UCA_GET_L1_W (uca_w_l13[i]));
6765  printf ("%04X.", UCA_GET_L2_W (uca_w_l13[i]));
6766  printf ("%04X.", UCA_GET_L3_W (uca_w_l13[i]));
6767  if (coll->uca_opt.sett_strength >= TAILOR_QUATERNARY)
6768  {
6769  printf ("%04X]", coll->uca_w_l4[cp * coll->uca_exp_num + i]);
6770  }
6771  else
6772  {
6773  printf ("]");
6774  }
6775  }
6776  }
6777  else
6778  {
6779  printf (" | Weight(Computed) : %04X", cp + 1);
6780  }
6781 }

6783 /*
6784  * locale_check_and_set_shared_data - checks if data has already been taken
6785  * into account as shared data, otherwise
6786  * adds the new key as shared data
6787  * Returns : error status
6788  * lsd_type(in): shared data type
6789  * lsd_key(in) : key (name) of data
6790  * data(in) : data to be stored for key
6791  * ldml_context(in): context of LDML file
6792  * found_entry(out): shread data entry if found
6793  *
6794  * Note : this is used in context of genlocale tool, to check for duplicate
6795  * collations, normalization or alphabet data
6796  */
6797 static int
6798 locale_check_and_set_shared_data (const LOC_SHARED_DATA_TYPE lsd_type, const char *lsd_key, const void *data,
6799  LDML_CONTEXT * ldml_context, LOC_SHARED_DATA ** found_entry)
6800 {
6801 #define SHARED_DATA_INCR_SIZE 32
6802 
6803  int status = NO_ERROR;
6804  int i;
6805 
6806  assert (lsd_key != NULL);
6807  assert (found_entry != NULL);
6808 
6809  *found_entry = NULL;
6810 
6811  for (i = 0; i < count_shared_data; i++)
6812  {
6813  if (lsd_type == shared_data[i].lsd_type && strcmp (lsd_key, shared_data[i].lsd_key) == 0)
6814  {
6815  *found_entry = &(shared_data[i]);
6816  goto exit;
6817  }
6818  }
6819 
6820  /* set new shared data */
6821  if (alloced_shared_data <= count_shared_data)
6822  {
6823  shared_data =
6824  (LOC_SHARED_DATA *) realloc (shared_data,
6825  sizeof (LOC_SHARED_DATA) * (alloced_shared_data + SHARED_DATA_INCR_SIZE));
6826  if (shared_data == NULL)
6827  {
6828  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
6829  status = ER_LOC_GEN;
6830  goto exit;
6831  }
6832  alloced_shared_data += SHARED_DATA_INCR_SIZE;
6833  }
6834 
6835  memset (&(shared_data[count_shared_data]), 0, sizeof (LOC_SHARED_DATA));
6836  shared_data[count_shared_data].lsd_type = lsd_type;
6837  strncpy (shared_data[count_shared_data].lsd_key, lsd_key, COLL_NAME_SIZE - 1);
6838  shared_data[count_shared_data].lsd_key[COLL_NAME_SIZE - 1] = '\0';
6839 
6840  if (data != NULL)
6841  {
6842  shared_data[count_shared_data].data = strdup ((const char *) data);
6843  if (shared_data[count_shared_data].data == NULL)
6844  {
6845  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
6846  status = ER_LOC_GEN;
6847  goto exit;
6848  }
6849  }
6850 
6851  if (ldml_context != NULL)
6852  {
6853  shared_data[count_shared_data].ldml_context.ldml_file = strdup (ldml_context->ldml_file);
6854  if (shared_data[count_shared_data].ldml_context.ldml_file == NULL)
6855  {
6856  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
6857  status = ER_LOC_GEN;
6858  goto exit;
6859  }
6860  shared_data[count_shared_data].ldml_context.line_no = ldml_context->line_no;
6861  }
6862 
6863  count_shared_data++;
6864 
6865 exit:
6866  return status;
6867 
6868 #undef SHARED_DATA_INCR_SIZE
6869 }
6870 
6871 /*
6872  * locale_free_shared_data -
6873  *
6874  * Note : this is used in context of genlocale tool.
6875  */
6876 void
6877 locale_free_shared_data (void)
6878 {
6879  if (shared_data != NULL)
6880  {
6881  int i;
6882  assert (count_shared_data > 0);
6883  assert (alloced_shared_data > 0);
6884 
6885  for (i = 0; i < count_shared_data; i++)
6886  {
6887  if (shared_data[i].data != NULL)
6888  {
6889  free (shared_data[i].data);
6890  shared_data[i].data = NULL;
6891  }
6892  if (shared_data[i].ldml_context.ldml_file != NULL)
6893  {
6894  free (shared_data[i].ldml_context.ldml_file);
6895  shared_data[i].ldml_context.ldml_file = NULL;
6896  }
6897  }
6898 
6899  free (shared_data);
6900  shared_data = NULL;
6901  }
6902 
6903  alloced_shared_data = 0;
6904  count_shared_data = 0;
6905 }

6907 /*
6908  * start_unicode_file() - XML element start function
6909  * "ldml unicodefile"
6910  *
6911  * return: 0 validation OK enter this element , 1 validation NOK do not enter
6912  * -1 error abort parsing
6913  * data: user data
6914  * attr: attribute/value pair array
6915  */
6916 static int
6917 start_unicode_file (void *data, const char **attr)
6918 {
6919  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
6920  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
6921  char *att_val = NULL;
6922 
6923  assert (data != NULL);
6924 
6925  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (pd);
6926 
6927  if (strlen (ld->unicode_data_file) != 0)
6928  {
6929  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "Only one unicodefile tag is allowed", -1);
6930  return -1;
6931  }
6932 
6933  att_val = NULL;
6934  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "CUBRIDUnicodeDataFilePath", &att_val) == 0)
6935  {
6936  assert (att_val != NULL);
6937 
6938  strncpy (ld->unicode_data_file, att_val, sizeof (ld->unicode_data_file) - 1);
6939  ld->unicode_data_file[sizeof (ld->unicode_data_file) - 1] = '\0';
6940  ld->alpha_tailoring.alphabet_mode = 1;
6941  ld->unicode_mode = 1;
6942  }
6943 
6944  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "", 0);
6945 
6946  return 0;
6947 }

6981 /*
6982  * locale_save_normalization_to_C_file() - saves normalization data
6983  * to C source file as variables, for later use
6984  * when generating the locale shared library.
6985  *
6986  * return: error code
6987  * fp(in): file pointer where to write the data
6988  * ld(in): locale data
6989  */
6990 static int
6991 locale_save_normalization_to_C_file (FILE * fp, LOCALE_DATA * ld)
6992 {
6993  int i;
6994  UNICODE_MAPPING *um;
6995  UNICODE_NORMALIZATION *norm;
6996 
6997  assert (ld != NULL);
6998  assert (fp != NULL);
6999 
7000  norm = &(ld->unicode_normalization);
7001 
7002  if (norm->do_not_save)
7003  {
7004  goto exit;
7005  }
7006 
7007  PRINT_VAR_TO_C_FILE (fp, "int", "unicode_mappings_count", norm->unicode_mappings_count, "%d",
7008  UNICODE_NORMALIZATION_DECORATOR);
7009 
7010  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "unicode_mapping_index", "int", "%d", MAX_UNICODE_CHARS, norm->unicode_mapping_index,
7011  UNICODE_NORMALIZATION_DECORATOR);
7012  PRINT_NUM_ARRAY_TO_C_FILE (fp, "list_full_decomp", "int", "%d", MAX_UNICODE_CHARS, norm->list_full_decomp,
7013  UNICODE_NORMALIZATION_DECORATOR);
7014 
7015  fprintf (fp, "" DLL_EXPORT_PREFIX "const UNICODE_MAPPING unicode_mappings_%s[] = {", UNICODE_NORMALIZATION_DECORATOR);
7016  for (i = 0; i < norm->unicode_mappings_count; i++)
7017  {
7018  um = &(norm->unicode_mappings[i]);
7019  fprintf (fp, "\t{%u, %d, ", um->cp, um->size);
7020  PRINT_STRING_TO_C_FILE (fp, um->buffer, um->size);
7021  fprintf (fp, "}%s\n", (i < norm->unicode_mappings_count - 1) ? "," : "");
7022  }
7023  fprintf (fp, "};");
7024 
7025 exit:
7026 
7027  return 0;
7028 }
7029 
7030 #define NORM_MAPPING_DUMP_MODE_FULL 0
7031 #define NORM_MAPPING_DUMP_MODE_COMP 1
7032 #define NORM_MAPPING_DUMP_MODE_DECOMP 2
7033 /*
7034  * dump_locale_normalization - dump the selected UNICODE_NORMALIZATION
7035  * structure in human-readable text format.
7036  * Returns : NO_ERROR.
7037  * norm(in) : the UNICODE_NORMALIZATION to be dumped in text format.
7038  */
7039 static void
7040 dump_locale_normalization (UNICODE_NORMALIZATION * norm)
7041 {
7042  int i;
7043 
7044  printf ("Sorted list of unicode mappings: \n");
7045  for (i = 0; i < norm->unicode_mappings_count; i++)
7046  {
7047  printf ("%d.\t ", i + 1);
7048  dump_unicode_mapping (&(norm->unicode_mappings[i]), NORM_MAPPING_DUMP_MODE_FULL);
7049  printf ("\n");
7050  }
7051 
7052  printf ("\n Unicode composition mappings \n");
7053  for (i = 0; i < MAX_UNICODE_CHARS; i++)
7054  {
7055  int j, comp_start, comp_end;
7056 
7057  printf ("CP: %04X | \t Comp: ", i);
7058 
7059  if (!CP_HAS_MAPPINGS (norm->unicode_mapping_index[i]))
7060  {
7061  printf ("NO\n");
7062  continue;
7063  }
7064 
7065  comp_start = GET_MAPPING_OFFSET (norm->unicode_mapping_index[i]);
7066  comp_end = GET_MAPPING_OFFSET (norm->unicode_mapping_index[i + 1]);
7067 
7068  printf ("(%2d) From: %d To: %d | \t", comp_end - comp_start, comp_start, comp_end);
7069 
7070  for (j = comp_start; j < comp_end; j++)
7071  {
7072  dump_unicode_mapping (&(norm->unicode_mappings[j]), NORM_MAPPING_DUMP_MODE_COMP);
7073  printf (" | ");
7074  }
7075  printf ("\n");
7076  }
7077 
7078  printf ("\n Unicode decomposition mappings\n");
7079  for (i = 0; i < MAX_UNICODE_CHARS; i++)
7080  {
7081  int decomp_idx = norm->list_full_decomp[i];
7082 
7083  printf ("CP: %04X | Decomp : ", i);
7084 
7085  if (decomp_idx < 0)
7086  {
7087  printf ("NO\n");
7088  continue;
7089  }
7090 
7091  assert (decomp_idx >= 0);
7092 
7093  dump_unicode_mapping (&(norm->unicode_mappings[decomp_idx]), NORM_MAPPING_DUMP_MODE_DECOMP);
7094 
7095  printf ("\n");
7096  }
7097 }
