7099 /*
7100  * dump_unicode_mapping() - Dump a UNICODE_MAPPING to the console.
7101  *
7102  * Returns:
7103  * um(in) : unicode mapping to dump
7104  */
7105 static void
7106 dump_unicode_mapping (UNICODE_MAPPING * um, const int mode)
7107 {
7108  unsigned int cp;
7109  unsigned char *next;
7110  unsigned char *cur_str;
7111 
7112  if (um == NULL)
7113  {
7114  printf ("Null mapping.\n");
7115  return;
7116  }
7117 
7118  if (mode == NORM_MAPPING_DUMP_MODE_FULL)
7119  {
7120  printf ("CP: %04X", um->cp);
7121  if (um->size > 0)
7122  {
7123  printf (" ->");
7124  }
7125  }
7126 
7127  cur_str = um->buffer;
7128  next = cur_str;
7129  while (next < um->buffer + um->size)
7130  {
7131  cp = intl_utf8_to_cp (cur_str, (const int) INTL_UTF8_MAX_CHAR_SIZE, &next);
7132  printf ("%04X ", cp);
7133  cur_str = next;
7134  }
7135 
7136  if (mode == NORM_MAPPING_DUMP_MODE_COMP)
7137  {
7138  printf (" -> CP: %04X", um->cp);
7139  }
7140 }
7141 
7142 /*
7143  * dump_console_conversion - dump Console text conversion data structure
7144  * in human-readable text format.
7145  * Returns : NO_ERROR.
7146  * tc(in): the TEXT_CONVERSION to be dumped in text format.
7147  */
7148 static int
7149 dump_console_conversion (TEXT_CONVERSION * tc)
7150 {
7151  unsigned char utf8_seq[INTL_UTF8_MAX_CHAR_SIZE + 1];
7152  unsigned char cnv_utf8_buf[2 * 3 + 1];
7153  unsigned char *cnv_utf8;
7154  CONV_CP_TO_BYTES *c_item;
7155  unsigned int utf8_cp, con_cp;
7156  unsigned char *next;
7157  int utf8_size;
7158  unsigned char *char_to_print = NULL;
7159  int err;
7160 
7161  if (tc == NULL || tc->conv_type == TEXT_CONV_NO_CONVERSION)
7162  {
7163  printf ("\nNo console conversion for this locale.\n\n");
7164  goto exit;
7165  }
7166 
7167  printf ("\nType: ");
7168  if (tc->conv_type == TEXT_CONV_ISO_88591_BUILTIN || tc->conv_type == TEXT_CONV_ISO_88599_BUILTIN)
7169  {
7170  printf ("built-in %s console to UTF-8 encoding \n",
7171  (tc->conv_type == TEXT_CONV_ISO_88591_BUILTIN) ? "ISO 8859-1" : "ISO 8859-9");
7172  }
7173  else
7174  {
7175  printf ("%s byte console to UTF-8 encoding \n", (tc->conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE) ? "single" : "double");
7176  }
7177 
7178  printf ("Windows codepages: %s\n", tc->win_codepages);
7179  printf ("Linux LANG charset values: %s\n", tc->nl_lang_str);
7180 
7181  if (tc->conv_type != TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE && tc->conv_type != TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_2BYTE)
7182  {
7183  goto exit;
7184  }
7185 
7186  printf ("\nConsole to UTF-8 conversion:\n");
7187  printf ("Console codepoint -> Unicode codepoint | Character (UTF-8) \n");
7188  for (con_cp = 0; con_cp <= tc->text_last_cp; con_cp++)
7189  {
7190  unsigned char dbcs_seq[2 + 1];
7191  int dbcs_size;
7192 
7193  if (tc->conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_2BYTE && con_cp <= 0xff && tc->byte_flag[con_cp] != 0)
7194  {
7195  printf ("%02X -> Undefined or leading byte\n", con_cp);
7196  continue;
7197  }
7198  utf8_cp = con_cp;
7199 
7200  if (con_cp >= tc->text_first_cp)
7201  {
7202  c_item = &(tc->text_to_utf8[con_cp - tc->text_first_cp]);
7203  utf8_cp = intl_utf8_to_cp (c_item->bytes, c_item->size, &next);
7204  assert ((unsigned char *) next - c_item->bytes == c_item->size);
7205 
7206  if (utf8_cp == 0x3f)
7207  {
7208  assert (con_cp != 0x3f);
7209  printf ("%04X -> Undefined codepoint\n", con_cp);
7210  continue;
7211  }
7212 
7213  utf8_size = intl_cp_to_utf8 (utf8_cp, utf8_seq);
7214  assert ((unsigned int) utf8_size < sizeof (utf8_seq));
7215  utf8_seq[utf8_size] = '\0';
7216 
7217  char_to_print = (utf8_cp > 0x20) ? utf8_seq : (unsigned char *) "";
7218 
7219  dbcs_size = intl_cp_to_dbcs (con_cp, tc->byte_flag, dbcs_seq);
7220  dbcs_seq[dbcs_size] = '\0';
7221 
7222  cnv_utf8 = cnv_utf8_buf;
7223  utf8_size = sizeof (cnv_utf8_buf);
7224 
7225  if (tc->conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE)
7226  {
7227  err = intl_text_single_byte_to_utf8_ext (tc, dbcs_seq, dbcs_size, &cnv_utf8, &utf8_size);
7228  assert (err == NO_ERROR);
7229  }
7230  else
7231  {
7232  if (dbcs_size == 2 && tc->byte_flag[dbcs_seq[0]] != 1)
7233  {
7234  /* invalid console codepoint */
7235  cnv_utf8 = NULL;
7236  }
7237  else
7238  {
7239  err = intl_text_dbcs_to_utf8_ext (tc, dbcs_seq, dbcs_size, &cnv_utf8, &utf8_size);
7240  assert (err == NO_ERROR);
7241  }
7242  }
7243 
7244  if (cnv_utf8 != NULL)
7245  {
7246  assert ((unsigned int) utf8_size <= sizeof (cnv_utf8_buf));
7247  char_to_print = cnv_utf8;
7248  }
7249  }
7250  else
7251  {
7252  utf8_size = intl_cp_to_utf8 (utf8_cp, utf8_seq);
7253  assert ((unsigned int) utf8_size < sizeof (utf8_seq));
7254  utf8_seq[utf8_size] = '\0';
7255 
7256  char_to_print = (utf8_cp > 0x20) ? utf8_seq : (unsigned char *) "";
7257  }
7258 
7259  if (con_cp <= 0xff)
7260  {
7261  printf ("%02X -> Ux%04X | %s\n", con_cp, utf8_cp, char_to_print);
7262  }
7263  else
7264  {
7265  printf ("%04X -> Ux%04X | %s\n", con_cp, utf8_cp, char_to_print);
7266  }
7267  }
7268 
7269  if (tc->text_last_cp < ((tc->conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE) ? (unsigned int) 0xff : (unsigned int) 0xffff))
7270  {
7271  if (tc->conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE)
7272  {
7273  printf ("Range %02X - FF is not mapped\n", tc->text_last_cp + 1);
7274  }
7275  else
7276  {
7277  printf ("Range %04X - FFFF is not mapped\n", tc->text_last_cp + 1);
7278  }
7279  }
7280 
7281  printf ("\n\nUTF-8 to console conversion:\n");
7282  printf ("Unicode codepoint [Unicode character] ->" " Console codepoint | Character (UTF-8 encoding)\n");
7283  for (utf8_cp = 0; utf8_cp <= tc->utf8_last_cp; utf8_cp++)
7284  {
7285  if (utf8_cp > 0x20)
7286  {
7287  utf8_size = intl_cp_to_utf8 (utf8_cp, utf8_seq);
7288  assert ((unsigned int) utf8_size < sizeof (utf8_seq));
7289  utf8_seq[utf8_size] = '\0';
7290  }
7291  else
7292  {
7293  utf8_seq[0] = ' ';
7294  utf8_seq[1] = '\0';
7295  }
7296 
7297  con_cp = utf8_cp;
7298  char_to_print = utf8_seq;
7299 
7300  if (utf8_cp >= tc->utf8_first_cp)
7301  {
7302  c_item = &(tc->utf8_to_text[utf8_cp - tc->utf8_first_cp]);
7303 
7304  con_cp = intl_dbcs_to_cp (c_item->bytes, c_item->size, tc->byte_flag, &next);
7305  assert (next - c_item->bytes == c_item->size);
7306 
7307  if (con_cp == 0x3f)
7308  {
7309  assert (utf8_cp != 0x3f);
7310  printf ("Ux%04X [%s] -> Not mapped\n", utf8_cp, utf8_seq);
7311  continue;
7312  }
7313 
7314  cnv_utf8 = cnv_utf8_buf;
7315  utf8_size = sizeof (cnv_utf8_buf);
7316 
7317  if (tc->conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE)
7318  {
7319  err = intl_text_single_byte_to_utf8_ext (tc, c_item->bytes, c_item->size, &cnv_utf8, &utf8_size);
7320  assert (err == NO_ERROR);
7321  }
7322  else
7323  {
7324  err = intl_text_dbcs_to_utf8_ext (tc, c_item->bytes, c_item->size, &cnv_utf8, &utf8_size);
7325  assert (err == NO_ERROR);
7326  }
7327  assert ((unsigned int) utf8_size <= sizeof (cnv_utf8_buf));
7328  char_to_print = cnv_utf8 ? cnv_utf8 : utf8_seq;
7329  }
7330 
7331  if (tc->conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE)
7332  {
7333  printf ("Ux%04X [%s] -> %02X | %s\n", utf8_cp, utf8_seq, con_cp, char_to_print);
7334  }
7335  else
7336  {
7337  printf ("Ux%04X [%s] -> %04X | %s\n", utf8_cp, utf8_seq, con_cp, char_to_print);
7338  }
7339  }
7340 
7341  printf ("Codepoints above Ux%04X are not mapped\n", tc->utf8_last_cp);
7342 
7343 exit:
7344  return 0;
7345 }
7346 
7347 #define BUF_PUT_INT16(buf,v) \
7348  do { \
7349  unsigned short nv = htons(v); \
7350  *((unsigned char *) (buf)) = ((unsigned char *) &nv)[1]; \
7351  buf = (char *) (buf) + 1; \
7352  *((unsigned char *) (buf)) = ((unsigned char *) &nv)[0]; \
7353  buf = (char *) (buf) + 1; \
7354  } while (0)
7355 
7356 #define BUF_PUT_INT32(buf,v) \
7357  do { \
7358  unsigned int nv = htonl(v); \
7359  *((unsigned char *) (buf)) = ((unsigned char *) &nv)[3]; \
7360  buf = (char *) (buf) + 1; \
7361  *((unsigned char *) (buf)) = ((unsigned char *) &nv)[2]; \
7362  buf = (char *) (buf) + 1; \
7363  *((unsigned char *) (buf)) = ((unsigned char *) &nv)[1]; \
7364  buf = (char *) (buf) + 1; \
7365  *((unsigned char *) (buf)) = ((unsigned char *) &nv)[0]; \
7366  buf = (char *) (buf) + 1; \
7367  } while (0)
7368 
7369 #define BUF_ALIGN(buf, align) \
7370  ((char *)((((UINTPTR)(buf) + ((UINTPTR)((align)-1)))) \
7371  & ~((UINTPTR)((align)-1))))
7372 
7373 /*
7374  * locale_compute_coll_checksum() - Computes the MD5 checksum of collation
7375  *
7376  * Returns: error status
7377  * coll_data(in/out):
7378  */
7379 static int
7380 locale_compute_coll_checksum (COLL_DATA * cd)
7381 {
7382  int input_size = 0;
7383  char *input_buf = NULL;
7384  char *buf_pos;
7385  int cp, w;
7386 
7387  if (cd->uca_opt.sett_expansions)
7388  {
7389  /* Weights L1-L3 */
7390  input_size += cd->uca_exp_num * cd->w_count * sizeof (cd->uca_w_l13[0]);
7391  if (cd->uca_opt.sett_strength >= TAILOR_QUATERNARY)
7392  {
7393  /* Weights L4 */
7394  input_size += cd->uca_exp_num * cd->w_count * sizeof (cd->uca_w_l4[0]);
7395  }
7396  }
7397  else
7398  {
7399  /* single level weights */
7400  input_size += cd->w_count * sizeof (cd->weights[0]);
7401  }
7402 
7403  /* next_cp */
7404  input_size += cd->w_count * sizeof (cd->next_cp[0]);
7405 
7406  if (cd->count_contr > 0)
7407  {
7408  /* contractions list */
7409  input_size += cd->count_contr * sizeof (COLL_CONTRACTION);
7410 
7411  input_size += sizeof (cd->contr_min_size);
7412  input_size += sizeof (cd->cp_first_contr_offset);
7413  input_size += sizeof (cd->cp_first_contr_count);
7414  }
7415 
7416  input_size += sizeof (UCA_OPTIONS);
7417 
7418  /* build buffer */
7419  input_buf = (char *) malloc (input_size);
7420  if (input_buf == NULL)
7421  {
7422  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
7423  return ER_LOC_GEN;
7424  }
7425 
7426  memset (input_buf, 0, input_size);
7427  buf_pos = input_buf;
7428 
7429  if (cd->uca_opt.sett_expansions)
7430  {
7431  for (cp = 0; cp < cd->w_count; cp++)
7432  {
7433  for (w = 0; w < cd->uca_exp_num; w++)
7434  {
7435  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, cd->uca_w_l13[cp * cd->uca_exp_num + w]);
7436  }
7437  }
7438 
7439  if (cd->uca_opt.sett_strength >= TAILOR_QUATERNARY)
7440  {
7441  /* Weights L4 */
7442  for (cp = 0; cp < cd->w_count; cp++)
7443  {
7444  for (w = 0; w < cd->uca_exp_num; w++)
7445  {
7446  BUF_PUT_INT16 (buf_pos, cd->uca_w_l4[cp * cd->uca_exp_num + w]);
7447  }
7448  }
7449  }
7450  }
7451  else
7452  {
7453  for (cp = 0; cp < cd->w_count; cp++)
7454  {
7455  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, cd->weights[cp]);
7456  }
7457  }
7458 
7459  for (cp = 0; cp < cd->w_count; cp++)
7460  {
7461  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, cd->next_cp[cp]);
7462  }
7463 
7464  if (cd->count_contr > 0)
7465  {
7466  /* contractions list */
7467  for (cp = 0; cp < cd->count_contr; cp++)
7468  {
7469  COLL_CONTRACTION *c = &(cd->contr_list[cp]);
7470 
7471  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, c->next);
7472  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, c->wv);
7473  for (w = 0; w < MAX_UCA_EXP_CE; w++)
7474  {
7475  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, c->uca_w_l13[w]);
7476  }
7477  for (w = 0; w < MAX_UCA_EXP_CE; w++)
7478  {
7479  BUF_PUT_INT16 (buf_pos, c->uca_w_l4[w]);
7480  }
7481 
7482  memcpy (buf_pos, c->c_buf, sizeof (c->c_buf));
7483  buf_pos += sizeof (c->c_buf);
7484 
7485  *buf_pos++ = c->cp_count;
7486  *buf_pos++ = c->size;
7487  *buf_pos++ = c->uca_num;
7488 
7489  buf_pos +=
7490  sizeof (COLL_CONTRACTION) - (2 * sizeof (int) + MAX_UCA_EXP_CE * sizeof (int) +
7491  MAX_UCA_EXP_CE * sizeof (short) + sizeof (c->c_buf) + 3 * sizeof (char));
7492  }
7493 
7494  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, cd->contr_min_size);
7495 
7496  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, cd->cp_first_contr_offset);
7497 
7498  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, cd->cp_first_contr_count);
7499  }
7500 
7501  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, cd->uca_opt.sett_strength);
7502  *buf_pos++ = (unsigned char) (cd->uca_opt.sett_backwards);
7503  *buf_pos++ = (unsigned char) (cd->uca_opt.sett_caseLevel);
7504  buf_pos = BUF_ALIGN (buf_pos, sizeof (int));
7505  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, cd->uca_opt.sett_caseFirst);
7506  *buf_pos++ = (unsigned char) (cd->uca_opt.sett_expansions);
7507  buf_pos = BUF_ALIGN (buf_pos, sizeof (int));
7508  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, cd->uca_opt.sett_contr_policy);
7509  *buf_pos++ = (unsigned char) (cd->uca_opt.use_only_first_ce);
7510  buf_pos = BUF_ALIGN (buf_pos, sizeof (int));
7511  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, cd->uca_opt.sett_match_contr);
7512 
7513  if (buf_pos - input_buf != input_size)
7514  {
7515  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("Error on collation checksum", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
7516  free (input_buf);
7517  return ER_LOC_GEN;
7518  }
7519  assert (buf_pos - input_buf == input_size);
7520 
7521  memset (cd->checksum, 0, sizeof (cd->checksum));
7522  md5_buffer (input_buf, input_size, cd->checksum);
7523 
7524  free (input_buf);
7525 
7526  md5_hash_to_hex (cd->checksum, cd->checksum);
7527 
7528  return NO_ERROR;
7529 }
7530 
7531 /*
7532  * locale_alphabet_data_size() - Computes the size required by alphabet data
7533  *
7534  * Returns: size in bytes
7535  * a(in):
7536  */
7537 static int
7538 locale_alphabet_data_size (ALPHABET_DATA * a)
7539 {
7540  int input_size = 0;
7541 
7542  input_size += sizeof (a->a_type);
7543  input_size += a->l_count * a->lower_multiplier * sizeof (a->lower_cp[0]);
7544  input_size += a->l_count * a->upper_multiplier * sizeof (a->upper_cp[0]);
7545 
7546  return input_size;
7547 }
7548 
7549 /*
7550  * locale_alphabet_data_to_buf() - Saves alphabet data to a buffer
7551  *
7552  * Returns: size in bytes
7553  * a(in):
7554  * buf(out):
7555  *
7556  * Note : this is used in for data checksum purpose
7557  */
7558 static int
7559 locale_alphabet_data_to_buf (ALPHABET_DATA * a, char *buf)
7560 {
7561  char *buf_pos = buf;
7562  int cp, m;
7563 
7564  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, a->a_type);
7565 
7566  for (cp = 0; cp < a->l_count; cp++)
7567  {
7568  for (m = 0; m < a->lower_multiplier; m++)
7569  {
7570  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, a->lower_cp[cp * a->lower_multiplier + m]);
7571  }
7572  }
7573 
7574  for (cp = 0; cp < a->l_count; cp++)
7575  {
7576  for (m = 0; m < a->upper_multiplier; m++)
7577  {
7578  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, a->upper_cp[cp * a->upper_multiplier + m]);
7579  }
7580  }
7581 
7582  return CAST_BUFLEN (buf_pos - buf);
7583 }
7584 
7585 /*
7586  * locale_compute_locale_checksum() - Computes the MD5 checksum of locale data
7587  *
7588  * Returns: error status
7589  * ld(in/out):
7590  */
7591 static int
7592 locale_compute_locale_checksum (LOCALE_DATA * ld)
7593 {
7594  int input_size = 0;
7595  char *input_buf = NULL;
7596  char *buf_pos;
7597  int cp;
7598 
7599  input_size += sizeof (ld->dateFormat);
7600  input_size += sizeof (ld->timeFormat);
7601  input_size += sizeof (ld->datetimeFormat);
7602  input_size += sizeof (ld->timestampFormat);
7603  input_size += sizeof (ld->timetzFormat);
7604  input_size += sizeof (ld->datetimetzFormat);
7605  input_size += sizeof (ld->timestamptzFormat);
7606 
7607  input_size += sizeof (ld->month_names_abbreviated);
7608  input_size += sizeof (ld->month_names_wide);
7609  input_size += sizeof (ld->day_names_abbreviated);
7610  input_size += sizeof (ld->day_names_wide);
7611  input_size += sizeof (ld->am_pm);
7612 
7613  input_size += sizeof (ld->day_names_abbr_parse_order);
7614  input_size += sizeof (ld->day_names_wide_parse_order);
7615  input_size += sizeof (ld->month_names_abbr_parse_order);
7616  input_size += sizeof (ld->month_names_wide_parse_order);
7617  input_size += sizeof (ld->am_pm_parse_order);
7618 
7619  input_size += sizeof (ld->number_decimal_sym);
7620  input_size += sizeof (ld->number_group_sym);
7621  input_size += sizeof (ld->default_currency_code);
7622 
7623  input_size += locale_alphabet_data_size (&(ld->alphabet));
7624  input_size += locale_alphabet_data_size (&(ld->identif_alphabet));
7625 
7626  input_size += sizeof (ld->txt_conv.conv_type);
7627  if (ld->txt_conv.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE || ld->txt_conv.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_2BYTE)
7628  {
7629  TEXT_CONVERSION *tc = &(ld->txt_conv);
7630 
7631  input_size += sizeof (tc->byte_flag);
7632  input_size += sizeof (tc->utf8_first_cp);
7633  input_size += sizeof (tc->utf8_last_cp);
7634  input_size += sizeof (tc->text_first_cp);
7635  input_size += sizeof (tc->text_last_cp);
7636 
7637  input_size += strlen (tc->nl_lang_str);
7638  input_size += strlen (tc->win_codepages);
7639 
7640  input_size += (tc->utf8_last_cp - tc->utf8_first_cp + 1) * sizeof (CONV_CP_TO_BYTES);
7641  input_size += (tc->text_last_cp - tc->text_first_cp + 1) * sizeof (CONV_CP_TO_BYTES);
7642  }
7643 
7644  if (!(ld->unicode_normalization.do_not_save))
7645  {
7646  UNICODE_NORMALIZATION *un = &(ld->unicode_normalization);
7647 
7648  input_size += MAX_UNICODE_CHARS * sizeof (un->unicode_mapping_index[0]);
7649  input_size += MAX_UNICODE_CHARS * sizeof (un->list_full_decomp[0]);
7650 
7651  input_size += un->unicode_mappings_count * sizeof (UNICODE_MAPPING);
7652  }
7653 
7654  /* build buffer */
7655  input_buf = (char *) malloc (input_size);
7656  if (input_buf == NULL)
7657  {
7658  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("memory allocation failed", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
7659  return ER_LOC_GEN;
7660  }
7661 
7662  buf_pos = input_buf;
7663  memset (input_buf, 0, input_size);
7664 
7665  /* formats */
7666  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->dateFormat, sizeof (ld->dateFormat));
7667  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->dateFormat);
7668 
7669  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->timeFormat, sizeof (ld->timeFormat));
7670  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->timeFormat);
7671 
7672  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->datetimeFormat, sizeof (ld->datetimeFormat));
7673  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->datetimeFormat);
7674 
7675  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->timestampFormat, sizeof (ld->timestampFormat));
7676  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->timestampFormat);
7677 
7678  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->timetzFormat, sizeof (ld->timetzFormat));
7679  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->timetzFormat);
7680 
7681  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->datetimetzFormat, sizeof (ld->datetimetzFormat));
7682  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->datetimetzFormat);
7683 
7684  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->timestamptzFormat, sizeof (ld->timestamptzFormat));
7685  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->timestamptzFormat);
7686 
7687  /* calendar names */
7688  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->month_names_abbreviated, sizeof (ld->month_names_abbreviated));
7689  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->month_names_abbreviated);
7690 
7691  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->month_names_wide, sizeof (ld->month_names_wide));
7692  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->month_names_wide);
7693 
7694  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->day_names_abbreviated, sizeof (ld->day_names_abbreviated));
7695  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->day_names_abbreviated);
7696 
7697  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->day_names_wide, sizeof (ld->day_names_wide));
7698  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->day_names_wide);
7699 
7700  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->am_pm, sizeof (ld->am_pm));
7701  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->am_pm);
7702 
7703  /* calendar parsing order */
7704  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->day_names_abbr_parse_order, sizeof (ld->day_names_abbr_parse_order));
7705  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->day_names_abbr_parse_order);
7706 
7707  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->day_names_wide_parse_order, sizeof (ld->day_names_wide_parse_order));
7708  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->day_names_wide_parse_order);
7709 
7710  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->month_names_abbr_parse_order, sizeof (ld->month_names_abbr_parse_order));
7711  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->month_names_abbr_parse_order);
7712 
7713  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->month_names_wide_parse_order, sizeof (ld->month_names_wide_parse_order));
7714  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->month_names_wide_parse_order);
7715 
7716  memcpy (buf_pos, ld->am_pm_parse_order, sizeof (ld->am_pm_parse_order));
7717  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->am_pm_parse_order);
7718 
7719  /* number symbols */
7720  memcpy (buf_pos, &(ld->number_decimal_sym), sizeof (ld->number_decimal_sym));
7721  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->number_decimal_sym);
7722 
7723  memcpy (buf_pos, &(ld->number_group_sym), sizeof (ld->number_group_sym));
7724  buf_pos += sizeof (ld->number_group_sym);
7725 
7726  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, ld->default_currency_code);
7727 
7728  /* alphabets */
7729  buf_pos += locale_alphabet_data_to_buf (&(ld->alphabet), buf_pos);
7730  buf_pos += locale_alphabet_data_to_buf (&(ld->identif_alphabet), buf_pos);
7731 
7732  /* text conversion */
7733  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, ld->txt_conv.conv_type);
7734 
7735  if (ld->txt_conv.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_1BYTE || ld->txt_conv.conv_type == TEXT_CONV_GENERIC_2BYTE)
7736  {
7737  TEXT_CONVERSION *tc = &(ld->txt_conv);
7738 
7739  memcpy (buf_pos, tc->byte_flag, sizeof (tc->byte_flag));
7740  buf_pos += sizeof (tc->byte_flag);
7741 
7742  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, tc->utf8_first_cp);
7743  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, tc->utf8_last_cp);
7744  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, tc->text_first_cp);
7745  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, tc->text_last_cp);
7746 
7747  memcpy (buf_pos, tc->nl_lang_str, strlen (tc->nl_lang_str));
7748  buf_pos += strlen (tc->nl_lang_str);
7749 
7750  memcpy (buf_pos, tc->win_codepages, strlen (tc->win_codepages));
7751  buf_pos += strlen (tc->win_codepages);
7752 
7753  memcpy (buf_pos, tc->utf8_to_text, (tc->utf8_last_cp - tc->utf8_first_cp + 1) * sizeof (CONV_CP_TO_BYTES));
7754  buf_pos += (tc->utf8_last_cp - tc->utf8_first_cp + 1) * sizeof (CONV_CP_TO_BYTES);
7755 
7756  memcpy (buf_pos, tc->text_to_utf8, (tc->text_last_cp - tc->text_first_cp + 1) * sizeof (CONV_CP_TO_BYTES));
7757  buf_pos += (tc->text_last_cp - tc->text_first_cp + 1) * sizeof (CONV_CP_TO_BYTES);
7758  }
7759 
7760  if (!(ld->unicode_normalization.do_not_save))
7761  {
7762  UNICODE_NORMALIZATION *un = &(ld->unicode_normalization);
7763 
7764  for (cp = 0; cp < MAX_UNICODE_CHARS; cp++)
7765  {
7766  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, un->unicode_mapping_index[cp]);
7767  }
7768 
7769  for (cp = 0; cp < MAX_UNICODE_CHARS; cp++)
7770  {
7771  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, un->list_full_decomp[cp]);
7772  }
7773 
7774  for (cp = 0; cp < un->unicode_mappings_count; cp++)
7775  {
7776  UNICODE_MAPPING *um = &(un->unicode_mappings[cp]);
7777  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, um->cp);
7778  BUF_PUT_INT32 (buf_pos, um->size);
7779  memcpy (buf_pos, um->buffer, sizeof (um->buffer));
7780  buf_pos += sizeof (um->buffer);
7781 
7782  buf_pos += sizeof (UNICODE_MAPPING) - (sizeof (um->buffer) + 2 * sizeof (int));
7783  }
7784  }
7785 
7786  if (buf_pos - input_buf != input_size)
7787  {
7788  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("Error on locale checksum", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
7789  free (input_buf);
7790  return ER_LOC_GEN;
7791  }
7792  assert (buf_pos - input_buf == input_size);
7793 
7794  memset (ld->checksum, 0, sizeof (ld->checksum));
7795  md5_buffer (input_buf, input_size, ld->checksum);
7796 
7797  free (input_buf);
7798 
7799  md5_hash_to_hex (ld->checksum, ld->checksum);
7800 
7801  return NO_ERROR;
7802 }
7803 
7804 /*
7805  * common_collation_end_rule() - finishes a collation rule
7806  *
7807  * Returns: error status
7808  * data(in/out): user data
7809  * ld(in/out): locale data
7810  * rule_id(in): collation rule id (position in rule list)
7811  * t_rule(in/out): collation rule
7812  */
7813 static int
7814 common_collation_end_rule (void *data, LOCALE_DATA * ld, const int rule_id, TAILOR_RULE * t_rule)
7815 {
7816  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
7817 
7818  assert (data != NULL);
7819  assert (ld != NULL);
7820  assert (t_rule != NULL);
7821 
7822  if (ld->last_rule_level != TAILOR_UNDEFINED)
7823  {
7824  if (ld->last_rule_level != t_rule->level)
7825  {
7826  /* first rule must match the level of anchor */
7827  pd->xml_error = XML_CUB_ERR_PARSER;
7828  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, "Rule level doesn't match reset level", -1);
7829  return -1;
7830  }
7831 
7832  /* reset level of anchor : don't need to check for following rules */
7833  ld->last_rule_level = TAILOR_UNDEFINED;
7834  }
7835 
7836  t_rule->direction = ld->last_rule_dir;
7837  t_rule->r_pos_type = ld->last_rule_pos_type;
7838 
7839  /* last tailor character is the new reference */
7840  if (!(t_rule->multiple_chars))
7841  {
7842  /* reset rule position */
7843  ld->last_rule_pos_type = RULE_POS_BUFFER;
7844 
7845  assert (t_rule->t_buf_size > 0);
7846 
7847  ld->last_r_buf_size = t_rule->t_buf_size;
7848  ld->last_r_buf_p = t_rule->t_buf;
7849 
7850  memcpy (ld->last_anchor_buf, t_rule->t_buf, t_rule->t_buf_size);
7851  ld->last_anchor_buf[t_rule->t_buf_size] = '\0';
7852  }
7853 
7854  /* BEFORE applies only for the first rule after <reset> */
7855  ld->last_rule_dir = TAILOR_AFTER;
7856 
7857  if (pd->verbose)
7858  {
7859  char msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE];
7860  int xml_line_no = XML_GetCurrentLineNumber (pd->xml_parser);
7861  int xml_col_no = XML_GetCurrentColumnNumber (pd->xml_parser);
7862 
7863  snprintf (msg, sizeof (msg) - 1, "* Rule %d, L :%d, Dir:%d, PosType:%d, Mc:%d ;" " XML: line: %d , col:%d *",
7864  rule_id, t_rule->level, t_rule->direction, t_rule->r_pos_type, t_rule->multiple_chars, xml_line_no,
7865  xml_col_no);
7866  PRINT_DEBUG_END (data, msg, 0);
7867  }
7868 
7869  return 0;
7870 }
7871 
7872 /*
7873  * common_collation_start_rule() - starts a collation rule
7874  *
7875  * Returns: error status
7876  * data(in/out): user data
7877  * attr(in): element name
7878  * ld(in/out): locale data
7879  * t_rule(in/out): collation rule
7880  */
7881 static int
7882 common_collation_start_rule (void *data, const char **attr, LOCALE_DATA * ld, TAILOR_RULE * t_rule)
7883 {
7884  char *ref_buf_p = NULL;
7885  int ref_buf_size = 0;
7886  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
7887 
7888  assert (data != NULL);
7889  assert (ld != NULL);
7890  assert (t_rule != NULL);
7891 
7892  assert (ld->last_rule_pos_type == RULE_POS_BUFFER);
7893 
7894  strcpy (t_rule->anchor_buf, ld->last_anchor_buf);
7895 
7896  /* reference is last reference or anchor if no last refence is available */
7897  if (ld->last_r_buf_p == NULL)
7898  {
7899  ref_buf_p = ld->last_anchor_buf;
7900  ref_buf_size = strlen (ld->last_anchor_buf);
7901  }
7902  else
7903  {
7904  ref_buf_p = ld->last_r_buf_p;
7905  ref_buf_size = ld->last_r_buf_size;
7906  }
7907 
7908  assert (ref_buf_size > 0);
7909  assert (ref_buf_p != NULL);
7910 
7911  t_rule->r_buf = (char *) malloc (ref_buf_size);
7912  if (t_rule->r_buf == NULL)
7913  {
7914  pd->xml_error = XML_CUB_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
7915  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "memory allocation failed", -1);
7916  return -1;
7917  }
7918  memcpy (t_rule->r_buf, ref_buf_p, ref_buf_size);
7919  t_rule->r_buf_size = ref_buf_size;
7920 
7921  return 0;
7922 }
7923 
7924 /*
7925  * start_include_collation() - XML element start function
7926  * "ldml collations include"
7927  *
7928  * return: 0 validation OK enter this element , 1 validation NOK do not enter
7929  * -1 error abort parsing
7930  * data: user data
7931  * attr: attribute/value pair array
7932  */
7933 static int
7934 start_include_collation (void *data, const char **attr)
7935 {
7936  XML_PARSER_DATA *pd = (XML_PARSER_DATA *) data;
7937  LOCALE_DATA *ld = NULL;
7938  XML_PARSER_DATA *new_pd = NULL;
7939  char *att_val = NULL;
7940  char include_file_path[PATH_MAX] = { 0 };
7941  char *prev_ldml_file = NULL;
7942  int prev_line_no = 0;
7943  LDML_CONTEXT *context = NULL;
7944 
7945  assert (data != NULL);
7946 
7947  if (xml_get_att_value (attr, "file", &att_val) != 0)
7948  {
7949  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR ("<include> tag requires a valid FILE attribute.", ER_LOC_GEN, true);
7950  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, "<include> tag requires a valid " "FILE attribute.", -1);
7951 
7952  return -1;
7953  }
7954 
7955  /* build a path and check if the file exists/is accessible */
7956  envvar_ldmldir_file (include_file_path, PATH_MAX, att_val);
7957  new_pd = xml_create_subparser (pd, include_file_path);
7958 
7959  ld = (LOCALE_DATA *) XML_USER_DATA (new_pd);
7960  assert (ld != NULL);
7961 
7962  context = &(ld->ldml_context);
7963  prev_ldml_file = context->ldml_file;
7964  prev_line_no = context->line_no;
7965  context->ldml_file = strdup (include_file_path);
7966  context->line_no = 0;
7967 
7968  if (new_pd == NULL)
7969  {
7970  char err_msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE] = { 0 };
7971 
7972  switch (pd->xml_error)
7973  {
7974  case XML_CUB_ERR_INCLUDE_LOOP:
7975  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg) - 1, "Inclusion loop found for file %s.", include_file_path);
7976  break;
7977  case XML_CUB_ERR_PARSER_INIT_FAIL:
7978  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg) - 1, "Failed to initialize subparser for file path %s.",
7979  include_file_path);
7980  break;
7981  case XML_CUB_OUT_OF_MEMORY:
7982  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg) - 1, "Memory exhausted when creating subparser for file %s.",
7983  include_file_path);
7984  break;
7985  }
7986  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (err_msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
7987  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, err_msg, -1);
7988 
7989  return -1;
7990  }
7991 
7992  xml_parser_exec (new_pd);
7993 
7994  if (new_pd->xml_error == XML_CUB_ERR_FILE_MISSING)
7995  {
7996  char err_msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE] = { 0 };
7997 
7998  snprintf (err_msg, sizeof (err_msg) - 1, "Included file %s does not exist or " "is not accessible.",
7999  include_file_path);
8000  PRINT_DEBUG_START (data, attr, err_msg, -1);
8001  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (err_msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
8002 
8003  return -1;
8004  }
8005  else if (new_pd->xml_error != XML_CUB_NO_ERROR)
8006  {
8007  char msg[ERR_MSG_SIZE] = { 0 };
8008  const char *xml_err_text = (char *) XML_ErrorString (XML_GetErrorCode (new_pd->xml_parser));
8009 
8010  snprintf (msg, sizeof (msg) - 1, "Error parsing file %s, " "line: %d, column: %d. Internal XML: %s",
8011  new_pd->filepath, new_pd->xml_error_line, new_pd->xml_error_column, xml_err_text);
8012  LOG_LOCALE_ERROR (msg, ER_LOC_GEN, true);
8013 
8014  return -1;
8015  }
8016 
8017  free (context->ldml_file);
8018  context->ldml_file = prev_ldml_file;
8019  context->line_no = prev_line_no;
8020 
8021  pd->next = new_pd->next;
8022  xml_destroy_parser_data (new_pd);
8023  free (new_pd);
8024 
8025  return 0;
8026 }
